review: nice place for lunch! went there with my frds,  lunch is not crazy as dinner,  the food always good! our waiter is very nice, all the thing from cheesecake factory are good!except their menu. i think they really need to clean their menu. Greasy

The wait was FOREVER. waited about 45 minutes for a table on a Sunday evening.  Food was decent, ordered Baja Chicken Tacos with a Shirley Temple. It was pretty filling after you eat the bread that is served for free. The cost is about the same as every other chain restaurants but it all depends on what you are in the mood to eat. As always, the cheesecakes are amazing!

I first ate at the freehold location in 2008 and wasnt impressed in the beggining due to a bad meal that I had.I ordered a wasabi crusted tuna thinking the tuna was a fresh  piece of yellowfin or ahi   was well done and not tasty at all.I wrote to the company and they apologized.I went back again for my bday lunch and ordered a skirt steak   was delicous but the main thing for me at cheesecake factory is the cheesecake,my favorite one on the menu is the adams peanut butter which has butterfinger pieces mmmmm so tasty since my first visit, I have been very satisfied with the cheesecake factory and will return again and again

For the most part, if you have been to one cheesecake factory you have been to them all.  Friendly staff, good food with huge portions.  And of course Cheesecake - yum.  Its always a tab pricey but I think you get what you pay for. It was nice to recently have visited and got to enjoy lunch without the kids for once.  My wife and I had a great time at this one in particular and look forward to going back.

Am I really about to leave a review for a chain restaurant? Yes, apparently I am. They deserve opinions and good (or bad) reviews too.  I've always been a fan of this place... huge portions and cheap prices, and the good is genuinely tasty. Apps, I love the Ahi tuna tartar, the avocado egg rolls, and the southwest chicken egg rolls. For the mains... I must, always must, get the Lousiana Chicken Pasta here. It is fantastic... thin, tender breaded parmasean chicken, with bow tie pasta, mushrooms, onions, and peppers in a spicy, creamy sauce. You can make this into two meals, but why bother? Enjoy the 2000 calories in one sitting... it is worth every calorie.

The food here is consistent with all other Cheesecake Factorys. It's a chain so of course if you have been to one you have been to them all. Anyway, I came here on a Monday night and this place was jam packed! First they gave us a beeper for the wait which I get and it's normal, but when our beeper went off they told us there was a line for people who had already had their beepers go off. So there were two waits which I found a little odd. The first wait was about 20 minutes (what the told us when we walked in) and the second wait was 5 minutes. Service was slow but I can't be mad at the waitress because every seat must have been taken. It took over 10 minutes to get our drinks after ordering them. If you are unfamiliar with the way this place is set up, all of their two seater tables are in a line about a foot away from each other. This was annoying because I was seated next to two very loud women and I could barely hold my own conversation with my friend because they were talking SO LOUD. That put me in a bad mood. I'm also a little irritated because after I had already been waiting about 15 minutes, I heard the hostess tell new people that were coming in that the hi-top tables in the middle were seat yourself and you would get service right away. If I had known I definitely would have sat myself there...

Yeah the family wanted to come here for a Saturday lunch, to me its just a okay place but for.the family they seem to like the place. The only thing I can say they have that I like is the sandwiches they offer. The place has a  nice decor and good service so that's a plus.

I've been to several Cheesecake Factories and this one um, literally takes the cake? (Sorry, bad joke) Honestly, though I am always skeptical of places with too large of a menu but every time I have eaten there everything has been extremely well-prepared and absolutely delicious. They have a fantastic "Skinnylicious" menu that enables you to eat well and also calorie-friendly. Sure, there's a wide range of salads but also samosas, tacos, ahi carpaccio, and lots of vegetarian friendly dishes. I'm fond of the shrimp and fresh arugula and endive salad (I don't see endive on menus too often and it's a nice treat if you happen to be a fan of it). One day, I'm going to make it to their Sunday Brunch because I hear they do a fantastic job with the omelettes. During the spring and summer season this is a great place to dine al fresco. The have a huge portico with vaulted ceilings that is softly lit and so comfortable to sit in that you usually wind up staying wayy past dinner has ended. That's ok though - because in addition to the selection of cheesecakes (White chocolate raspberry truffle and Reese's PB pie are my favorites) they also have a full bar with a nice array of specialty cocktails. The cucumber martini on a warm, summer night is my favorite.

Yeah, I love the food in this place. It is so super-sizingly good, and the menu is so huge, there is literally something for everyone. My experience there was as expected-long wait to be seated, friendly and prompt service, cheesecake for desert that made me sleepy for an hour afterwards, and a not so painful bill at the end. Aside from eating way more calories than you'd usually want to, this Cheesecake Factory location is a solid choice.

I am normally not a chain restaurant eating person but since I had never been to a Cheesecake factory before, thought I would give it a try.  The first time we attempted to go, it was a weekend fir dinner and there was a 2.5 hr wait!  The high tables in the bar and the bar seats are first come first serve and not a spot here was clearing anytime soon.  We did not want to wait so we came back a few weeks later on a Sunday at 1pm.  Although there was still a 30 min wait, we were able to get a spot at the bar right away.  The decor is very inviting and warm.  As we looked through the menus, I was overwhelmed by the variety and slightly confused as what kind of food the Cheesecake factory focuses on.  Identity crisis I must say.  I looked thru both the regular menu and the skinny menu.  After hearing how big the portions are and how the calories could really add up here, we sort of kept to the skinny menu.  We were impressed!  I started off with a skinny mojito and hubby ordered a skinny sangria.  What made the mojito "skinny" is that they use sweetener vs regular sugar or sugar syrup.  It was refreshing and surprisingly tasted like a normal mojito.  The husband ordered a skinny sangria which he really wasn't raving about.  The skinny in this is that no fruit is added.  From the reg menu, I ordered the lunch miso salmon with a side of sautéed spinach which I paid extra for.  It was delicious and the portion was still sufficient considering it was a lunch item.  I highly recommend the miso salmon.  Hubby ordered 2 items:  ahi carpaccio fr the skinny menu and the tex mex egg rolls fr the reg menu.  Was super impressed with the ahi carpaccio---for the portion size and tastiness, I'm afraid to say this of a chain restaurant, but its the best!  Nothing special about the Tex mex eggrolls---tasty but not any worse or better than other tex mex rolls I've had.  To finish off our Cheesecake factory experience,  I took a look at the dessert display case and the menu and man, the variety of dessert is insane!!!  We ended having the caramel macadamia cheesecake which was very good but probably would choose a different dessert if I ever returned so I could get my nose in something new. Tip:  avoid a long wait and go during off times

Their cheesecake is great! I really like their avocado egg rolls too! Their alfredo and chicken is mediocre because the noodles and sauce are decent but their chicken is so dry! I tried it twice in hopes that it was just a mess-up but nope. The two times I ordered it, the chicken let me down. :(  Oh well! If you enjoy cheesecake, this is the place to go for dessert! It is on the pricey side though. But, it a good place for special occasions because of the environment. :)

Love Cheesecake Factory, but not at this location. I've never experienced such poor service in my life. We sat down about 4:40 and the waiter came right away to bring us water and said he'll give us time to look over the menu and told us we can still get lunch menu for a cheaper price (lunch ends at 5 here) and I wanted the lunch special. About 10 minutes before 5, he came to take our order. We told him we were ready and he said that he'll be right back. What I mean be right back was that he went in and out the kitchen so many times I lost count and even took peoples orders who sat down after us. A couple minutes after 5 he finally came and I asked him if I can syill get lunch and he said that lunch is over. I am not a difficult person trying to look for discounts but in this case this just was not fair just waiting and waiting and him taking of people who came after us when everyone in my party was ready to order. I told him nicely about this and gave me the lunch special. I guess he got offended and never came back to the table once to check on us or ask if we needed anything The next time he came to the table was to drop off the check. Another waiter brought out everyone's food. It was some friends and I so the bread went fast, and we had to ask other waiters and the busboy for more bread. I wanted to tell the manager about my experience, not to look for a free meal on my next visit but so this waiter can get his act together and provide better service to future customers, but I didn't want to bother because I'm out of my friends and old enough to get over this and enjoy the rest of this night. This Cheescake Factory provides the worst service. Other locations provide provide you excellent service. Trust me go to the one in Menlo, Bridgewater, or Short Hills and stay away from the Freehold location.

So I found myself coming to another cheesecake factory restaurant, this time with my two middle girls, ages 6.5 and 8. Well as in typical fashion, if your there for a table, you'll need to wait about 15min. Not that bad.. We were seated at a decent booth and Anthony greeted us.  We ordered for the kids and I ordered the firecracker salmon. Well when they delivered the firecracker salmon, I must say.. Compared to All the other Cheesecake factory restaurants I have been to, this dish they served me looked empty.. As though someone ate most of it... See the photo... I will post another photo, when I am in Boston next week. They usually serve it with a very large mound of cabbage in the middle.. I mentioned this to the waiter.. I asked home "what happened to this dish? Did someone eat from it?" LOL He seemed concerned... So I explained and he called over the manager. I once again explained.. And expected All Cheesecake factory restaurants to be consistent.. He stated that is how they serve it there always and asked if I wanted something else.  I stated, no I love that stuff and was just surprised at the difference.. Well for anyone that hasn't tasted this dish here.. I think it is heavenly.. The cabbage is a red cabbage that has some tangy spicy Thai type sauce on it.. I love it. You also dip the salmon in it and it great.. My 8yr old had asked to change her order about 10 minutes after she ordered it... And Anthony was very nice about it and swapped it out. When we were done eating, Anthony offered complimentary desert cheesecakes on the house for the three of us in compensation for the disappointment. I must say, they did redeem themselves with their excellent customer service.

Normally I'm a fan but my last visit on 4/27 I was so not happy!   Our waiter was practically unconscious...my entree was awful!  I NEVER send anything back but my ahi tuna salad was the stuff that food poisoning was made from!   Then I had to wait 15 min for someone to offer me something else.   I will probably go back just cause it's local..... : ((

Flies, flies and more flies!  I went for lunch with my husband and three kids.  We were already at the mall, so we figured it was convenient.  I have to say that my husband and I used to go there regularly on our Saturday night date night.  We would find a place at the bar and eat there, since the wait for a table was always at least an hour.  The bartenders were great - they were friendly and fun, and always seemed to remember our favorite drink.  The bar was crowded, but that's ok for a Saturday night.  It was fun!  However.....We stopped going after a disastrous mothers day brunch.  The food was awful - I mean every dish went back.  The manager apologized profusely and tried to make it right.  After two tries with the food (French toast...not a tough one right?  All either burnt or undercooked) we gave up.  When we received our bill, the manager deducted almost everything.  We left the waitress a big tip anyway - she tried. So fast forward... After so many months, we figured we would give it another chance.  Big mistake.  We were seated in a booth along the back of the restaurant that was adjacent to the kitchen.  Since the kitchen is behind a great wall of windows, we can see in, which I usually consider a good thing.  Nothing to hide, right?  Well, this time, the windows were crawling with flies.  Not a few, not several....MANY, MANY flies.  It was repulsive.  My husband noticed it first, and once we all looked, we couldn't stop.  I do not know how that kitchen was functioning with so many flies in there.  Needless to say, none of us really touched our food. The hostesses are very sweet, our server was fine.  Not friendly, not rude.  I don't see any reason to go back.  It is a beautifully decorated space for a chain, and the menu is extremely extensive.  But after two horrendous experiences, we would be better off elsewhere.

We have all been to The Cheesecake Factory (yes ALL - even those friends that do ironic stuff, drink PBR, talk about bands that you've never heard of, and avoid chain establishments), so I am going to spare you the ambiance, atmosphere, and how there was a 45 minute wait and they don't take reservations.  By now, you know that their menu is pretty extensive, so what I try to do is try something different whenever I am here, even though I have my favorite burgers and pastas here (The Factory Burger and Pasta Jambalaya in case you are wondering). Since I haven't been out in months, due to recently becoming a baby daddy, from what they told me on Maury, I decided to try something new. From the appetizers menu, I ordered the avocado egg rolls.  Very nice concept - 2 green and 2 red ingredients - avocado, cilantro, sun dried tomatoes and red onions -are the star of this show.  This comes with a spicy cashew sauce that has a nice kick to it, similar to what they have at a mongolian grill.  Very nice. For the entree, I couldn't decide between salmon and steak, so I got both.  I am not sure who was in charge of presentation that night or what was going through their mind, but the entree plate had 3 turd-like shapes on it - the salmon, mashed potatoes, and the steak. The herb crusted salmon tasted like it was either marinated or oversteamed in asparagus, which goes hand in hand with the turd shapes, as it resembles a nice urine-like aroma.  A good piece of salmon doesn't really need to be marinated much - add some olive oil and freshly squeezed lemon juice and you are done.  Can't say this was a smash hit for me.   Steak Diane? Whoever was putting this number together at corporate on the menu had an ex-wife named Diane that probably took him for all he was worth because this definitely resembled the taste of self-pity and depression.  If you take a look at the picture I posted, you can barely call that a steak.  There were 6 or 7 little pre-cut pieces (probably because whoever was manning the grill didn't know how to cook to order), swamped in mushrooms.   This was a 2.5 out of 5 star entree altogether, but being out for the first time in months, drinking adult beverages like a nice Pear martini w/ Grey Goose and being on a date with my wife boosted this review to 4 stars.

Cheesecake factory, you all know you secretly love the place. A place to get decent food...any type of food actually. Mexican, Asian, American, Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, etc! A little overwhelming, but all the food is decent nonetheless. Chicken alfredo is garlicky goodness. I usually get a salad (Sante Fe this time). We always have enough to doggie-bag and eat leftovers for lunch the next day.  I was a little sad because there was no pumpernickel bread in our basket. I asked the server and he said they were out! C'mon cheesecake factory! Side note: wait times on weekends (we went Friday night) are long! We got into the Factory around 8:30, and had a 40 minute wait. Don't come starving or you'll order everything on the menu once you're seated!

Love cheesecake. Nothing crazy about them but they have a wide variety of food to try which is always awesome. Love the skinny menu!! Great options for less caloric intake. If you have no idea where you want to eat or what to eat go to Cheesecake Factory, there is so much to pick and you will find at least one thing you want!
Decent food and decent prices, the service is always good & the snickers cheesecake was great!

I've only had good experiences at this location. Yes, there's a wait during peak times, but that's not really something to complain about - what do you expect of a popular chain restaurant attached to a huge, frequently crowded mall? Just put your name in and go shopping for awhile; there's more than enough stores to browse and I've found that the waiting time is often less than what they say it'll be. The location is clean and well-kept. The outdoor area is very nice in the summer. Service is friendly. Speed is okay. They're very busy so the waiters and waitresses are always running around. As for the food, it's the same as any other Cheesecake factory. Enormous portions, calorie-laden, and decadently delicious and calorie-laden. Even the salads are enormous; I always, always have leftovers, sometimes enough for two more meals. Come for lunch for lower prices and more reasonable portions; don't worry, you'll probably still have leftovers anyway! Or come for dinner and just order multiple appetizers for the table and share them instead of getting entrees; the appetizers are also enormous! I LOVE their shepherd's pie; it's my absolute favorite for lunch. Four cheese and pasta da vinci are also good for lunch. Drinks are uber sweet and contain a good amount of alcohol - they're delicious if you don't mind lots of sugar. I'm a fan of the passion fruit mojito in particular. Obviously, the cheesecake is awesome too. They're all amazing but I recommend the 30th Anniversary Chocolate Cake Cheesecake. I didn't think I would like it (looked a little boring to me), but it was WONDERFUL. One of my favorite chains. Higher prices and the wait are well worth the large, delicious portions. Definitely good for a rare treat; don't go too often, as the food is very unhealthy. I know giving 5 stars to a chain is frowned upon by some people, but the thing is, this is New Jersey, not New York City. I can always get a delicious meal and have a good time at the Cheesecake Factory, and I can't say the same for the local Applebee's or other local restaurants.

I've had bad experiences here in past bc of long waits since this is a very busy location.  This time here got seated in 10 minutes even though it seemed lots of people waiting on tables.  We hade Pre movie Drinks and dessert. Everything was fine. Prompt service got the orders right and checked on us the right amount.  The Asian Pear Martini was delicious but I didn't really like the Raspberry martini.   I tasted some of  my wife's Lemon Drop martini and it was good.  The red velvet cheese cake was great and tiramisu cheesecake was just ok.
The hostess at this one was rude and nasty if I hadn't of been to a Cheesecake Factory before I would've left.  She needs an attitude adjustment.  The food was great though
Yes it's a chain but I love this place. Amazingly broad menu. All dishes perfected. Large enough portions to share and who doesn't love about 50 desert choices??? Khale salad one of my favorites.

First I want to say: I love the cheesecakes there!!!!! And I like sitting outside in summer because I don t like the air conditioning everywhere. It s just too cold! But outside it s nice. I was there many times and friends of mine had problems with the check because the waiter just took more money than he was supposed to. And another waiter needed three tries to split the bill the right way. So the bottom line is: Beverages and food perfect, service not so good.

If you like chain places this place is ok.  The cheesecakes use to be alot better but this place is just ok.  Being in freehold nj, there is always a long wait so it might be better to look elsewhere.  Food is overall good and drinks are well made.  They have excellent sandwichs and appys.
Everything is always fresh!!!  Happy hr is great $5 apps n drinks fantastic!!!

I have only eaten here a handful of times and haven't been in so long until now. Of course their menu is super long it's like reading a novel. Haha. Anyway, went for lunch with a friend and sat outside! Very nice except for something falling from the side of the building onto my plate. That doesn't bother me just took it off but it was pretty funny. Anyway, we got two different sandwiches and shared. We got the grilled chicken and avocado club without bacon. It was just ok. It pretty much just a grilled cheese sandwich which hockey and tomato on it. Nothing special. The the other sandwich was a southwestern grilled chicken. This was really good. The jalapeño peppers on it were pretty damn strong so if you like spicy you'll love it. I did have to take some of the peppers off bc it was too much for me but a delicious sandwich.  I also love how you have a choice of fries or garden salad with the sandwiches. We got the garden salad side and it came with a balsamic dressing which was good but of you want another type of dressing then ask bother didn't ask what type we want.  Bread is also served which he asked if we wanted first before bringing it. It was pretty soft and fresh!

I really do like this place, but I have to say, no matter what, their menu is just TOO LONG. It feels like unless you already know what you like, finding something "new" to try will take hours because you have to get though their menu. Overall, all of these chain places are the same. I've never had a problem at this particular one in Freehold. The service has always been good and I've always enjoyed how well they cook, plate and serve their food. I think the drinks are a bit overpriced, and as an avid drinker (LOL), I think they short you a lot on alcohol. I know I will be back and have updates, periodically. If you have never been, it's an absolutle must-it's not all about the cheesecake! ;)
Like this place. Their food and service always decent. I ordered the chicken almond salad sandwich last time, it taste pretty good but the toast very oily.

Mediocre at best. It's always packed and honestly it is not worth the hour and a half wait, I'd rather go to PF Changs. The tables are too close together that you feel like you're with the people sitting next to you. The menu is just WAY too extensive, how can you decide what to eat. I've never had anything here that I would rave over. It's your typical chain restaurant with lousy service and blah food. If that's your thing, then this is the place for you. Seriously, though, go to the other restaurants in that area rather than this one.

Went yesterday for Happy Hour.  Pretty sluggish atmosphere but the waiter was pleasant. We say at a small booth. He wasn't familiar with the 'well drink' liquors so he asked the bartender. We took our time ordering from the happy hour menu. He was fine with that. Sliders were excellent.  We ordered a second round of drinks and sliders.  The calamari was awesome and the Vietnamese spring rolls hit all the right notes. Plan to go back next week!

We went to the CF in Freehold this weekend. Originally we were sat at a small table outside near a heat lamp that was on very high. We asked the waitress to turn it down since it was pleasant 70 degrees outside and she said other customers who were bundled up nearby requested it. We asked to be moved to a different table and the waitress gave us an attitude. We went inside to the host stand and were seated at a bigger table outside with a different waitress who was very helpful. We ordered the Viatnamese shrimp summer rolls to share, and two salads (Chinese chicken for him, Luau for me). The food was very good, as usual. We will definately return.

This has become one of my all time FAVORITE restaurants! I try something new each time (both entree and appetizer) and have yet to be disappointed. Their menu is HUGE, but the creative variety makes it all the more appealing, not overwhelming as some large menus can be. Every single category is packed with choices, from appetizers, to entrees...desserts and cocktails! I really think they nailed it with providing choices for just about everyone, whether you are there for dinner, drinks, or just dessert (or all 3!). They have unique features to their menu that I feel set them apart. I think their "Skinny" menu is GREAT, a lot bigger than some other places I have seen, and satisfying as well. I especially love the section on the menu, "Small Plates" because it is perfect for sampling! You can taste a couple different items without filling up before your meal. I usually do this in place of an appetizer, this way I can still enjoy their delicious bread (the pumpernickel is the best!).  Of course, they are known for their delectable cheesecake, and seriously, you cannot go wrong! Honestly, I truly don't care for cheesecake at all, BUT they have so many options that sound so dreamy that I just had to try one...and I have to say I LIKED it because it was not the traditional cheesecake flavors you see most places (strawberry, NY style, chocolatey, etc). So, for me to actually like cheesecake, that says A LOT! Though, I must add their strawberry shortcake is heavenly!!!  If you haven't been here yet, you DEFINITELY must go!!! I don't see how anyone can be disappointed!!

Went here while at the Freehold Mall.  It was just me and my wife which is great because the place is always packed.  Walked up to the counter and told them we were only a table of two and they told us they could sit us immediately.  Smaller parties for the win!   I got the fish tacos and she got her favorite which is the chicken parm sandwich.  The portions here are always much more than you likely need to eat so the price will usually equal out the amount of food you get here.  I will say I'm not a big guy so if you are used to eating 4 tacos and full sides then maybe you don't feel the price is fair.  I actually felt that the tacos were good they had great flavor and I loved the slices of avocado on the top.  The problem was that they put so much taco sauce and other toppings on them I had to eat them with a fork.  I tried to pick up the first one and it just fell apart.  Not a huge issue just weird to order tacos and end up using your fork and knife.    My wife always likes the chicken parm sandwich which she can only eat one half of and takes the other half home.  I've tried it a few times and for a place like The Cheescake Factory they do a pretty decent take on this type of sandwich.  I really like to call Cheesecake Factory a chain diner.  The menu is so huge and they have so many different types of food.  I can go in and have an all Mexican style dinner or have an all Italian dinner.  With that in mind there is nothing that I find on the main menu that blows me away, but I've also never had anything that was not good either.  For dessert we had the red velvet cheesecake.  I have to be honest I have never ordered dessert here before this time.  The cheesecake slice much like the meals was huge and between the two of us we couldn't even finish it after our dinners.  With what I said in my previous paragraph I can see why they call this place the Cheescake Factory.  I really feel out of all the different options they have available on the menu the dessert was very good and stands out.  I'd recommend going here for anyone that is at the mall or in the area.  Like I said I like the food and to add on we have never had bad service either. Check it out.

There was gum in my mashed potatoes.  Chewed-up gum. I didn't discover it until I was eating the leftovers I brought home - so I'm not certain as to whether it was in the potatoes the whole time, or if an employee spit it in while packing my leftovers, conveniently so that I wouldn't have the ability to complain to the staff since I wouldn't find it until I got home. It's not even like we gave the wait staff a hard time - no changing orders around, no being rude, we were polite and simple customers.  Frankly, even if we weren't, that behavior isn't acceptable, but that's the only rationalization I could even begin to come up with. There's plenty of other great places to eat by the mall.  This one is not worth it.

Because of a gift certificate I  received for Christmas, I went here exactly twice. The first time was just OK, which in itself is unacceptable for the prices they charge. When you pay for high end, you expect high end. My food was just OK, and one of the breads they brought out before the meal was pretty nasty. The wheat bread was good, but the white bread was the most disgusting bread I ever tasted. The second time, I got the smokehouse burger, with extra barbecue. First, we got a TINY amount of Barbecue, and I got tired of asking for more. Second, despite asking for medium, it came out a disgusting raw. When I finally tracked down our waitress, she took it, and brought it back 20 minutes later. It was the same burger, and it was still pretty rare. I gave up and ate it. The onion rings I got with it were way undercooked, and disgusting. Burger King Onion Rings would have been a huge step up. Instead of just getting onion rings properly cooked, the waitress wanted to bring me something else instead. I guess she knew something I didn't. I got mashed potatoes. With a ton of salt, they were passable, but not great. My wife had a similar experience. There was no manager anywhere to be found, but as we were leaving, I saw a bunch of suit-types hanging out in back. We were going to get desert, but thought twice about that. NEVER coming back to this location. EVER.  I REALLY wanted to like the Cheesecake Factory. I like the look of the place, and the menu has some nice items. I might try another Cheesecake Factory in another location, but never again in life at the Freehold location. If I had a choice between paying DOUBLE for a McDonalds meal, or going here for free, I'd go to McDonalds. The fact the prices are so inappropriately high is just an extra insult. I think some of my friends are fooled, thinking that, if you pay a lot, it MUST be good, and if it's not, my friends are too insecure to admit it. I'm happy to pay extra for a good meal (Best ever waiter and meal experience was at the Melting Pot in Chestnut Hill, PA), but this is just horribly unacceptable. Send Chef Ramsay here! If you want decent cheap dining, you might be better off sticking to Chili's, TGIFridays, Applebees, etc. Charlie Browns is a nice slight step up. Even Friendlys, Chipotle or fast food is better.
this is one of the best spots for happy hour! $5 apps and drinks? With the quality service and food that comes from most Cheesecake factory restaurants this is one of the best deals around!

Avocado eggrolls are my jam. I make a meal out of them. The nachos meh I've had way better. The only thing negative about the eponymous cheesecake is that there are soooo many options to choose from your head almost explodes from delectable indecision. The cheesecake gets five stars just because if you don't like one, keep going till you find one you like. It's a chain and not a mom and pop place so you know you're not getting the best cheesecake ever but it is very, very good. Someone needs to open a Cannoli Factory... Service is good but when it's busy you can get forgotten about or treated in a hush and rush way, but hey it's jersey...we don't really do friendly here. The ambiance is good with the dark lighting but the seating is basically you breathing on your neighbor's plate. Overall great place once you find the dish you like and you can spend a few visits until you find your favorite types of cheesecake.

Ordered a Mai Tai with Lunch  $10.95. For real? Cost more than my Lunch.  I think I've had a drink in Manhattan for less Food was OK. They seat to many at once in the same section, so the Waiter was confused  Lots of screaming kids. I don't mean a fussy baby.  Parents these days don't seem to care what kids do or how loud they are  The seats are real close together here  Very Loud.  If your looking for a quiet relaxing meal this is not the place
We have been to more than our share of "Factory's" and this one (Freehold NJ) is no different. Great food, great service and clean. It's a bit noisy, aren't they all? That's not a problem for us.

Today I went here for the first time and was very much excited to try their food. I ordered Fettucini Alfredo for me and kid's pasta for my son. To my disappointment, both the pastas were very salty.way tooo saltyyy. I wonder how they could put that much salt and that too in a kid's meal.when I researched on the net, it seems few others also have the same experience but in different locations. I would not go back here. Waste of time and money.chicken samosa for the appetizer was good.but not worth the wait time they have.good bye Cheesecake Factory!

Food was good. Food could have come out a little quicker. Service was average. Overall the restaurant had a feminine feel to it. They had a completely separate menu with "skinny" options. The menu also had dress ads in it. I guess we ordered off the fat menu. The staff was wearing summer white pants including the men. Only 2 Tvs at the bar area and they were small. It's someplace 2 women go before shopping. It can have an emasculating effect if you are a man.

A very disappointing lunch.  We both ordered salads, and both salads were missing multiple ingredients.  One of the salads was served with the wrong dressing. Service was slow, and we were never checked on by the server to see if we needed anything.  The silverware wasn't clean.   Sad, I used to really enjoy the Cheesecake Factory.  It seems that the chain isn't what it used to be.

Came here this past weekend with my wife to celebrate an Annivesary.  For a Friday evening, they were very accomodating.  Considering our request to sit outside.  Server was very pleasant and provided bread to us immediately.  Provided an adequate amount of time to look over the menu.  Ordered the Bang Bang Chicken & Shrimp, which was very tasty.  Wife got the chicken and biscuits platter, which was equally as good.  It was basically everything we expected.  Generous portions, but expensive.  Would come back, as I liked that we were sat immediately.

We went there on Labor Day. Very disappointed to see how filthy the Ladies room was, paper all over the floor, no toilet paper in the stalls. Main dining room floor was wet and had toothpicks and butter wrappers and other debris all over it. Surprised to see that this seems to be an ongoing problem and that  management does not seem to care! Go someplace cleaner.

I like CCF. I do. Haven't eaten here in a while.....I ordered the wrong thing on this particular day....tonight I had the shrimp scampi/salmon combo. I was really disappointed. This was a dish I had eaten a few times in the past......Wish I didn't pick this.....the 3 HALF shrimp they plopped on my plate were over done, and swimming in a sea of, I guess what they consider to be scampi sauce.....the piece of salmon was tiny as well.....for the price $20.95, it was not a lot of food at all...I'm starving. I wish I ordered the -grilled chicken bacon avocado Swiss sandwich...next time CCF........
Love this plc. whole bunch of friends came here to celebrate us moving to "monmouth county" and I have to say I'm impressed. good food, good drink, good attitude!!!

I've been going to Cheesecake Factory  restaurants for years and I must say I was disappointed with this one but let me start with the positives.  Our server was very friendly and very attentive with our specific needs that my wife and I made for our meals.  From there, it went downhill.  My wife ordered an appetizer salad and wanted to bring it out together with my meal.  Unfortunately the salad came out about 10 minutes early but hey it happens.  Then when my tomato basil pasta dish came,  everything was wrong.  I didn't want the fresh mozzarella or pesto sauce added to my dish per request.  They sent it back and when I received my new dish, it was nowhere near what it looked liked before and basically the presentation didn't live up to the "cheesecake factory" standards.  I made these complaints to the manager there and basically was specifically explained that and I quote "I don't know why our kitchen couldn't handle your requests. I'll be sure to talk to them".  I was then expecting a discount like most restaurants would give for messing up your order but basically was fed some BS excuse and swore to never go to this location again.  I probably should give 1 star but the service was fair and she did apologize.  It's just some poor management on customer service but that's why you go to these chain restaurants.  You just better hope nothing is wrong with your order.  Good luck!

Curbside-to-go service... this a joke in Freehold! This restaurant is either not properly staffed and or poorly managed.  If curbside is requested, and the request is accepted, then the service should be delivered.  If they can't do it or there will be a major delay, the customer should be informed and given the choice to do something else...before arriving! Otherwise, the order should be free.

Every time I go to the Cheesecake Factory it is with a group (5 or more).  Everytime I have been there, and it is well over 20, there is never a problem with the food, and everyone is happy.  It is not 5 star, but it is above average. The only downside is the wait to get a table. The prices are reasonable and the portions match the prices.

Go on a weeknight because the wait on weekends in unbearable. Excellent Ahi tuna, excellent Asian chicken salad and yummy mango iced tea. The bread that they put out on the table is also out of this world. My only complaint is the noise. Not the place to have an intimate dinner.

The mac'n'cheese fried app is delicious. (2 stars because of them!) Everything else is eh. The alfredo sauce is super garlicy. I ordered the cordon blue omlette, it was ok, I don't think it was worth the $12. The potatoes that came with it were overly fried, I was surprised that they don't have bottles of ketsup (I got a small cup instead), and there was no jelly for the toast.
For a mall Americana experience, it is pretty darn good guys.   I aint gonna lie, food is great, service is ok, menu is huge. Drinks are pricey though.

Worst service i've had a restaurant, let alone a Cheesecake Factory. Our waiter was extremely unenthused, rushed us, had no communication with us, and was extremely rude. My food came out fine, but my dad's eggplant sandwich was solid as a rock, which he did not enjoy at all. I've been here before and the service was alright, but I've experienced much better service at the locations in Edison and Short Hills. We should have gone to PF Chang's down the way, as we had the opportunity to with no wait.

I used to come here a lot because I used to live around the area, so Freehold Mall was the go-to mall! I loved Cheesecake Factory as a teenager because the menu is amazing! I has a HUGE variety of food and ethnic cuisines, ranging from Mexican egg rolls, Italian pasta, Chinese chicken, Japanese sushi, to many more! I still enjoy the food here, but having been to so many fine restaurants in NYC, Cali, and other places, I would say that Cheesecake is a good place for a quick fix and if you're in the area. It's definitely a great place to hangout and enjoy happy hour with your friends or enjoy a meal before or after shopping.  Sometimes, this restaurant can get very packed, especially during dinner time! Overall the service is decent! Not the most attentive during dinner hours, but it is better than the average service.  I have to say that the drinks, food, and cheesecake menus are AMAZING! It's always a struggle to pick that one piece of cheesecake to wrap up the meal! Also, you can order cheesecakes to-go, which is very nice! The decors are very nicely designed, and the booths are very comfy and high, which gives you a lot of privacy!

In the world of customer service and management you are supposed to make customers happy. I had an e gift card with 2 free slices of cheesecake that didn't activate til January 1st which was in the fine print that I didn't see. I don't live close by and I was going to be Christmas shopping so I politely asked the manager if he could just let me use it. What's the difference if I use it now or next week...?? Then had a sarcastic comment made afterward. I'm sorry but that's not how business is done.

This restaurant is a giant hit or miss, sometimes it is good to decent and other times it is just horrible. It looks clean but when you get close it is very dirty. When i went in the bathroom there was poop in all toilets and throw up all over one stall, it looks like it has not been cleaned in months! The only great thing is the pumpernickel bread in the beginning.

This is a solid Cheesecake Factory location. The great thing about Cheesecake Factory is that their menu is huge and you have a lot of options. The bad thing about Cheesecake Factory is that their menu is huge and you have a lot of options. I am an indecisive person so I usually stick to their "skinny" menu because it's not as overwhelming, less calories and the food is really good! My favorite item off the skinny menu is the fish tacos with the side of vegetables and a mojito.  During the warmer months this Cheesecake Factory location offers outdoor dining which faces a few other stores, restaurants and one of the mall entrances. It's a great place for people watching. Even though you are essentially next to a parking lot, the outdoor decor is nice and you forget that.  Can you come to Cheesecake Factory and not order a cheesecake? Well, most times I don't but when I let myself indulge I really enjoy the banana cream cheesecake with fresh banana slices on top. Honestly, this slice of cheesecake is a meal in itself.  On National Cheesecake Day (yep, it exists!) the Cheesecake Factory offers a free slice of cheesecake with the purchase of the meal.

It's the cheese cake factory! Need I say more? ... Ok maybe a little more. This place has a super large menu  so there is something for everyone it's really a good place to eat when you want large great tasting entrees without the concern of how many calories you are stuffing your face with! Random fact: one of the entrees was over 2000 calories! 0-o  Any-who, if you are watching your calories ( ok, on this day I was) you want something a little light on the calories but heavy on the taste. For that they have a separate menu called the Skinnylicious menu. All the items on the menu ( including appetizers, drinks, & entrees) have the calories posted next them. The menu is a nice size too, so you are not only selecting from 4/5 options. I chose the Lemon-Garlic Shrimp. It came with asparagus and what seemed like a cup of pasta. This was about 560 calories. Which I appreciated. The flavor was a little -Meh and lacked taste. Like you could definitely tell it was diet food. I didn't really love it, but I didn't really hate it either. I do however, hate how close they sit you next to other people when you are seated on the bench with the one chair facing the table. I don't want people I don't know listening to my conversation & I sure as hell don't want to hear their conversation!
Small amount of fish in the fish tacos. Guess that was good though since the fish tacos tasted like dishwater. At least the server brought the drinks quickly.

I went to the Cheesecake Factory for the first time in a few years.  I think I stopped going because the food is sub-par. Sadly, nothing has changed.  While the service is fine, but special, the food has degenerated into TGI Friday quality. My kids had southern fried chicken sliders and chicken finger kids meals.  All the chicken was dry.  Plus the fingers are awfully small vs the fingers at other restaurants. I had the stuffed chicken tortillas and replaced the black beans with cilantro rice.  They must have made 10 lbs of rice early in the day and have it sit in a hot pan becuase it was DRY! The chicken tortillas were layers of dryness with soggy corn tortillas. The spicy chicken has absolutely ZERO SPICE.  It is a bit of sauce, but still dry. The only good thing was the corn cakes, which where moist and the sweetness of the corn shone through. My wife had a shrimp and bacon club which she liked. We will not be back for a few years at the least.

My fiancee and I have gone to this location many times and usually it's good but this past Sunday was terrible.  I don't know if management is just different on Sundays but everything was surprisingly bad.  I order the BBQ burger (which was good, no real complaints there) and she got the cobb salad.  Salad comes with no dressing on side like requested.  Nor did the salad contain avocado, bacon or blue cheese.  NICE COBB SALAD THERE, RIGHT?  After several minutes of trying to get the server's attention, who by the way, never once refilled my soda which had been empty for 15 minutes, she says she'll have the order fixed.  Salad comes back, brought by a "manager" but still missing bacon.  We inform the server later that the salad was still missing the bacon and barely got an apology, forget about some sort of accommodation on the check.  Full price for everything.   The other reason I mention the management was the fact that both the men's and women's restrooms were filthy.  Guess everything is lax on Sundays there, so be forewarned.  I highly doubt we'll be returning any time soon.  Very disappointing.

Took the family out to dinner, placed our orders and 3 of the 4 entrees came to the table, waited another 15 minutes for the 4 entree and when it came out the pasta was too salty.  Although we were not charged for the 4 meal it was disappointing to see my daughter wait to eat her meal and then not enjoy it.  Waitress was courteous, but we likely will not return for some time, as there are other establishments to try.

Food is excellent. Large portions. My favorite is four cheese penne. But pasta with meat sauce is good. Sliders are good. It's all good. Oreo cheese cake is heaven. If you go to this one ask to be seated with Curt or Veronica. Two of the best servers.

The wings are amazing here. I've been here a couple of times and I've never been disappointed yet. There are so many different cheesecakes to choose from for dessert. I would recommend this place to everyone.

Our experience was amazing!! Our waitress Elizabeth was phenomenal at accommodating our party of 13 people. The food was brought out in a very efficient and timely manner. Not only that the food was delicious, I would recommend this location and our waitress to anyone!

Have to defend this place over some of the neg reviews here.Its a CHAIN. I don`t expect alot out of a chain,however I`ve been to `bad` `touristy` CF`s elsewhere and `mall` ones like this.I can tell you in multiple visits,we`ve had consistently good food, decent service and constant refills. We did not ever find the place dirty (maybe a little haggard on the floors after a busy lunch service). Our only complaint usually is we are so full by the time we are done with the large portions we don`t get a chance usually to get the actual Cheesecake. We had one miscue last year by the wait staff that resulted in a free dessert,primarily b/c we DIDN`T complain like the table next to us. It``s decorated nicely and for a chain we go here when the entire party is undecided about what to eat and when we are sick of red sauce

Cheesecake is a chain, so their level of amazing is limited by the ability to switch things up. As for food, I just don't understand why corporate allows the menu to be 100+ pages. You ask for a menu and they give you the torah. Menu items vary from poor to amazing and most really fall along the adequate line. Personal favorites include the miso salmon and chicken madeira. I also like the cx ceasar salad and daily soup selection. Besides the food, the décor is standard -  kind of a semi-dressed up ambiance but nothing spectacular. Good for kids and groups, but I wouldn't really want to come here on a date (not very impressive...) Service has also ranged from spotty to good, but never great. In the world of chains, I'd say cheesecake is OK, but I've definitely experienced better. Also, beware of this location! As many have reported previously, lines are long to get in and I personally don't feel it's worth the wait!

Went last week or probably my third time ever. Finally learning how to order there. The entrees are so huge I can never finish however a nice soup and app works for me while the teenagers can down an entire meal. Good service and clean and fast.

Food was OK, but really overpriced. Service was poor. Server seemed like she would rather be doing something else, and just wanted to get us out of there. She seated us, took our order, and once we got our food we were basically ignored unless we waved our arms to get someones attention. When she did finally make it over (after we finally got her attention), started picking up plates off the table that we were not finished eating off of yet!  Avoid sitting in the outdoor "heated" patio. We sat there on a cool day, and the "heat" apparently doesn't work throughout. They had propane patio heaters out there, but only a few were lit and it got kind of chilly. They also seem to have a yellow jacket nest somewhere in the vicinity, as we had them buzzing around our food the entire time we were there.  I won't be back. Overall miserable experience.

This place has always been solid for us. The food is good, the decor is nice. It can get busy but we have been fortunate to get in without much wait. As I said the food is good and the portions are plenty. I haven't had a bad meal here. The menu has plenty of options so everyone should be able to find something. And then there are the desserts. Their cheesecake is delicious. Tons of options. The pumpkin cheesecake is outstanding. Sometimes we go to just get dessert. The pieces are generous. In my opinion this place is solid for a good meal. If you haven't been definitely give it a try.

Avocado Spring rolls are insanely good! Huge menu and has something for everyone. Even the iced tea is really good. Love how they have a ton of things on the menu and it all is really good. Good fish, good salads, they really have everything.

The atmosphere is cute, the lights are dim the music is pleasant. I was jamming & eating which equals happiness. Lol. My country fresh salad was good the lettuce tasted as though they needed to be washed though, but I liked the ingredients in it, just wish my greens were clean . The mini crab bites were really good. I'm waiting on my four cheeses pasta with chicken. If it's not good I'll let y'all know, otherwise it was yummy.

Waited over 40 minutes for an appetizer that was never put into the kitchen. Filthy wine glasses. Asked for ID twice before being served a damn beer at the bar. Did not get what I peered (by this time I just took what they provided to me)  Complained to managers, very nice to get a $7.00 damn appetizer off our bill. 2 meals, appetizer and two glasses of wine, $47? Actually, the appetizer was complementary thanks  to the cheesecake factory!! ($54 for that?!) oh and the red wine was cheap, boxed wine ($9 a glass, and a dirty glass at that)

Food was good the service sucks!! Waited 15 minutes for our drinks then 25 minutes after our appetizers we were still waiting for our main dish. No manager ever came over to explain except for the cheesecake why go back. when I finally spoke to the manager oh sorry her assistant said I apologize I was supposed to come over well he didn't they lost me as a customer and I will be calling the corporate office eat somewhere else.
Went here the other day for an anniversary dinner. Steak was one of the best I've had. Sangria was watered down and ridiculously overpriced ($11). Overall a nice experience.

I used to love cheesecake factory. In the past year, I found out that I am gluten intolerant so I was super excited to find out that they do a gluten free version of their pasta. I had the gluten free pasta divinci...I did not get sick afterwards, however the dish falls way under expectations when you've had the real one. The sauce isn't as creamy and the dish overall just doesn't taste the same. If you have a gluten allergy, steer clear of their gluten free pasta and go with one of their other dishes.

When we got here I was an hour wait which turned into an hour and a half because the hostess forgot to page us. We then got a table but had to wait another 20 min for food and at this point we were just really to eat our hands but when the food arrived it was great I just wish the service was bettter

What a treat! I love this restaurant. There is something on the menu for everyone. Whether you are counting calories or indulging in your favorite pasta The Cheesecake Factory never fails. Service can be on the slower side at times but it's worth the wait. Restaurant and Bathrooms are very clean . I would recommend calling ahead on weekends.

Above average chain restaurant My family enjoys it Love the small plate appetizers Fried cheese, fried zucchini, crab cakes, bang bang shrimp Nachos are a good value....huge plate Chicken Madeira is my favorite entrée Free soda refills are a nice touch Never had a bad dessert, all the cheesecakes are well made

I used to really like the cheesecake factory.  Then they took my favorite entrée off the menu (pork tenderloin) and I tried as hard as I could to find something I liked as much, but I couldn't.  After a lot of unsatisfactory meals, I stayed away. Shoot forward 6 years.  I went to the Freehold Cheesecake factory.  Snowy Sunday night, so there was no wait.  That's where the good ended.  It took about 15 minutes for a waitress to come.  Ok...we're in no hurry...don't stress..... why ruin an experience.  I order a Red Sangria and my boyfriend orders a beer.  We put in app (Cuban spring rolls and beet and goat cheese salad) and dinner orders (chicken Madeira and Bacon bacon burger).  The waitress comes back 10 minutes later with two waters and tells us she has to go get our drinks and bread.  She comes back with bread and we wait another 10 minutes for drinks. Honestly, this review would be so long I'd bore myself writing it.  Suffice it to say that the service stank for the entirety of the meal and the food was sub par (sangria tasted like fruit punch, bland salad, greasy spring rolls, gummy mashed potatoes, odd textured chicken, tasteless burger (3 different types of bacon, yet it didn't taste as much like a bacon burger as it should).... decent fries. There are so many other places that I could've spent the same amount of money and gotten a much, much, better meal.  I guess I'll try it again in another 6 years.

Slow service but all around good food. The music and atmosphere here is way to loud I had to keep asking my girlfriend what she said. Also being so close to everyone else's table is annoying since you can hear their conversations and they can hear yours.

Today we got lunch and it wasent bad at all! We enjoyed a friend Mac and cheese, simmosas, and some shrimp rolls! Everything we tasty but we were not blown away. I would like to come back a try some dinner meals!!

I haven't been to this place since 2011. I went today (December 1st, 2015) and I loved it! Our server Andrea was amazing. She made us feel welcome and didn't mind at all that we were taking a longer time to order since the menu is so big! We ordered the egg roll sampler and all I can say is WOW! We loved one of the sauces so much, the kitchen bottled one up for us! I got the spicy chicken sandwich which was divine. My sister got the Mac n cheese burger which was phenomenal! Finally, my mother got the chicken parm sandwich which, was also amazing. We were all so full we couldn't get desert! However, my mom got a piece of mango key lime cheesecake to go and it was delicious. This place is amazing! The inside is really nice. A little overpriced but hey, you get what you pay for.

Overall I am a fan of the Cheesecake Factory. The ambiance is very nice and the food is almost always very good. However, let's face facts - it's right next to the Freehold Raceway Mall, so it is almost ALWAYS super crowded and there is almost always a wait time. Mentally prepare yourself for this beforehand. And if you have any illusions of getting in on a Friday or Saturday night around dinnertime... well, all I can say is think again.  The menu is ENORMOUS. The menu is so big, IT HAS PAGE NUMBERS. When I have to refer to a dish that is "halfway down on page 12" for a friend to find what I am looking at, this means the menu is too big. I'm all for selection, don't get me wrong, but damn, this thing needs a table of contents and an index in the back. All kidding aside, it's a pretty expansive menu, so set aside a good 15 minutes to go through it and select what you want to eat. Bread as a starter is a nice touch, and has always been nice and hot for me. Appetizers are good (my friend loves the Avocado Egg Rolls), but don't forget the "small plate" options too as a starter - a lot of these look awesome, cost less than actual appetizers, and come with a ton of food.  Entrees have always been good for me. I personally recommend the pasta carbonara and chicken and biscuits here - sorry I don't have the menu page numbers to refer you to.  Service is spotty at best. It's a big place, with a LOT of tables, so your server has their hands full, no pun intended. Taken with a grain of salt (also no pun intended), it's not that big of a deal. Just don't expect to get out of here in a hurry. Prices are a little high, but again, it's Freehold, and at the mall. Expectations, people.  I would give this place 3.5 stars overall. As long as you know what you're getting into, its a really decent place to get a bite to eat.

My husband and I went here last week because we were given a gift card. We checked in with the hostess and were told 65-85 minute wait, and to come back in 30 minutes for our buzzer. We went to shop for awhile and came back. We waited the full 85 minutes before getting seated. The food at this place is decent, but I can't give it more than 3 stars because 1- the food is not worth the wait 2- the service is hit or miss. Most of the staff seems to be young and not very service oriented. We watched a group of women who had ordered apps at the bar then their buzzer went off,come up the the hostess stand only to be told their table wasn't ready yet. A server brought their app out to them and handed it to them and made them stand there holding it. The server just shrugged her shoulders and walked away. The women looked around like they didn't know what to do standing there trying to hold this large plate and their drinks. I will say the cheesecake is delicious and something you can't get anywhere else. So many choices!! You can walk in and get this to go so I would definitely go back to take out some cheesecake!
Every time I come here the food is fabulous. Most of the time there is a wait, and I always wait... It's so worth it. I try to order something new each time and I'm always impressed.
Great food, a bit pricey, but you get a lot. The selection can be overwhelming. The Sheppards Pie is good, also super soups and great hamburgers

We came here for an early dinner because we wanted to beat the storm and the crowd and got seated immediately. I wasn't too hungry so I ordered the Ahi Tartare. It was delicious! My daughter and I were fighting to eat it. It's Raw Tuna with Avocado and Soy Ginger Sesame Sauce with some deep fried wonton like chips. Daughter had the Shrimp Scampi and loved it. She loved the white wine in it. Hubs had the Fish Taco with a side of rice and beans. He liked it but thought the rice was a bit hard. Service was friendly and quick. Love that this place is in the neighborhood but it's so hard to get into because of the crowds!

The food here is very savory and has lots of bursting flavor! I just wish that there were more options that were a little more healthy for the fitness-freak inside of men. The cakes here are all made very well, and while they can get a little pricey, they're still very delicious

I'm a big Cheesecake Factory fan; partly because of their large menus and I know that I can always find something good to eat. Sadly though, this location is one of the poorer ones I've eaten at. We showed up and were shown right to a table, only to then sit there for a good 10 minutes before anyone came over to get our drink order. I ordered a beer and my wife a water and at the same time we put in our food order. It took a bit, but finally the drinks came by and eventually their famous bread basket followed...with only one type of bread as we were told they didn't have any wheat bread. While waiting for our food, we saw everyone else's bread go by, with both types of bread...odd. For our food we ordered two apps to share. One came out followed by the other about 10 minutes later. The food itself was good and up to their typical standards. It just seemed like the service as a whole was very disjointed and off. Nothing terrible, just not the best.

If i could rate this place a zero i totally would. Our server Vanessa was awful very robotic with the greet NEVER checked on us we had to ask other servers for more water and napkins. The food was not cooked all the way but trying to find our server was mission impossible. Worst experience of my life never returning.

Food is consistent. Typical of a large chain restaurant. Cheesecake is good, expensive and fattening but its cheese cake so that answers that question. Wouldn't be my first choice in places to go, but would still go back. Large salads, and Fried Mac and Cheese balls were real good.

Love the food and service the wait can be lengthy however their is always room at the high tops near the bar if your tastebuds can't be put on hold. The salads are my favorite And the burgers are delicious over a salad.

I'll never get the big fascination with this place for the life of me. I like the way the place is decorated, but that's about it.  My latest visit of course found us waiting for a table. We were given a 15 minute wait time and knowing their track record, I didn't expect it to actually happen. They actually called us right at the 15 minute mark!!  (yes, I was timing them)  we were seated and a waitress took our drink orders.  We then ordered our meals.  Took a half hour to be served and we didn't see the waitress till that point.  I had one of the factory combinations. Steak Diane and herb crusted salmon. The steak had a pretty good taste, all 2 ounces of it!! It was literally 3 pieces of beef each the size of a quarter!! The rest was all mushrooms and onions. The salmon was more like a piece of frozen salmon that they covered in pesto. It was kind of watery as if it had been frozen and thawed upon cooking, which I'm sure it was.  Mashed potatoes were good, but I could have lived without the 3 pieces of ice cold asparagus.  My wife had some fried shrimp over pasta. The shrimp were very greasy. Our son had the chicken enchiladas. Nothing to write home about there either.            Here is what I think is a major problem with this place. The menu is just too big!!  There is no way you can offer that many items and make everything fresh. That means that a lot of the stuff is frozen or pre-prepared.  Cut back on the menu size and do everything fresh and well.  I'm sure that will never happen because no matter what I say, the place is always packed.

Our experience at this Cheesecake Factory was superb! The waiter was amazing and the food was fantastic. We were skeptical to come back only because the menu changed and we lost our favorite menu items in the change. The skinnylicous menu was phenomenal and my husbands replacement to the caramel chicken was fabulous as well! I love that they have healthier options to choose from. We loved it! We will definitely be back. (And the cheesecake wasn't bad either *wink*)

The food was good but the bathrooms were both a wreck.  Totally unacceptable at a place like this.  The person in charge of that should be fired.  Paper all over the floor, no toilet paper in ANY stalls, men or women, and the floor all over the restaurant is slippery, like its greasy and hasn't been cleaned.  A couple of us slipped.  Also, I mentioned to our waitress that it was my birthday and not even a "happy birthday", as we heard another table having happy birthday sung to them.  All in all, a disappointment when I chose to go there on my birthday, on vacation.
Good for franchise food. They have a huge selection. It's always a bit overpriced. Crowded more in winter.

We had a party for eight and the gentleman I believe his name is Daniel was our waiter. He was excellent. He kept on top of all the orders and he served us all at a reasonably same time frame. The food was very well proportioned. In other words, huge! Lol.  The atmosphere is really chill and I really like the ambience. The service was excellent and I noticed they are very customer service oriented. If you don't like something they will switch it out for you. I would definitely go back.

Their cheesecakes are amazing. They have over a page of cheesecakes on their menu for you to choose from. I've also had pasta dishes from here. I have never had anything that I didn't like. The Mac and cheese balls (appetizer) are so delicious!

Went on a Sat night with 6 people. Was seated right away because we opted to sit outside which wasn't cold at all because they had heated lamps and heat coming from the ceilings.  I ordered the Bang Bang chicken and Shrimp which is my favorite dish here but there are so many things to order on the menu. They also have a skinny menu which gives you food and drink options which have less calories.  The calamari is one of the best that you can find at any restaurants. Perfectly cooked, not chewy at all.  The buffalo blasts was also a delicious appetizer. It was nice and crunchy on the outside with a nice buffalo sauce once you cut into it which allowed for the chicken not to be too dry.  And of course you have to try the cheesecake. Got the strawberry cheesecake. I'm not a fan of the cheesecake with all the works like the Oreo Extreme deluxe cheesecake which my brother got. but both of us described our cheese cake as very creamy and delicious.  There are so many cheesecakes to choose from!!

Food drinks and service are always good. Its a shame everything on the regular menu is 1000 calories plus... I guess most chains are like that. Skinny menu is pretty solid, as long as it holds true to the nutrition info.
The service was very bad. When we complained to management they laughed in our faces. We left not very happy. Some one needs to call there corporate office and complain.

Sigh. Showed up around 1:15 pm on a Sunday afternoon. It was busy but we decided we'd just eat at the bar since we thought it would be faster. It was...for everyone at the bar who wasn't us. We got our drinks pretty quick and the bartender took our order after serving our drinks. Close to 40 minutes later, my husband called the bartender over and asked what the status was with our food (mind you, it was a salad and a brunch order of french toast). He said he'd check on it. And apparently it was coming out "now". Five minutes later, still no food, an increasingly cranky husband, the manager comes over with her fake sweet voice saying it's just being "finished" (umm...i thought it was coming out) but would we like something else in the meantime like soup or a salad. Um - no. We want the food we ordered. The same food we see people all around us being served, many whom arrived very long after us. Finally, at about 53 minutes after ordering the food arrives. My guacamole salad was good. His french toast was tasty but I could have easily argued it was VERY underdone in the center. I didn't because what would the point have been? We got the bill and they did NOTHING for the long wait. So the bartender got a crappy tip which left me feeling badly but he did nothing to address the long wait, only apologized after we pointed it out and did nothing to improve the situation. Will definitely NOT be back.

My fiance and I came for lunch with our Daughter. The food was ok at best.  My main issue with this place was the bathrooms. They were absolutely filthy!!! I can't believe that they don't have a staff member to at least check them throughout the day. There was toilet paper all over the floor in all of the stalls and urine all over every toilet seat. I ended up holding my daughter in the air to let her go to the bathroom. I left there absolutely disgusted.
This place is beautiful and great for kids. The food is always good but very pricy at the end, all the little things add up.

Me and my fiancé eat here all the time but after our last experience we won't be coming back ! The food was fantastic and our waitress ( Elizabeth ) was awesome however the party next to our table " 15 people " took over a 100 pictures with the flash on and instead of confronting them we asked management if they could please ask them to stop ... The manager ( Esti ) said no but we can move you ?!?!? Wait what ? I have never seen such weak management and be told there's no " no flash policy " ... This pretty much ruined the night and left both of us heated and not wanting to go back ... Too many other places to spend our money.

My fiancé and I just left this location, he also is writing a review..... This is how awful our experience was, let me start off by saying our server (Elizabeth) was great no complaints with her, we were seated and ordered drinks and apps along with dinner and instantly noticed this party of 15 we're adjacent to us and taking literally hundreds of photos so instead of myself walking up to them and making a scene we decided to be nice and asked the server if there was anything that could be done and she said she would get a manager..... In the meantime 25 more photos were taken.... Anyway the "manager" Esti which is apparently new gets to our table and we express our dismay with the situation and ask if non the less they could tell them to turn off the flash especially due to the fact it was beaming right into my eyes, given me a migraine, and ruined our dinner..... Her response oh yeah sorry but I cannot ask them to not take photos. My fiancé then asks her so there is no policy against hundreds of flashes in a restaurant from an actual camera not cell phone... Once more her response... No there's nothing really I can say about it. She did not even try to rectify the situation in ANY WAY WHAT SO EVER other then saying oh well we can move YOU guys, yes move us while we are in the middle of dinner due to the fact that you are unable to perform you're managerial duties. Then walked away. Just great right. Then to top things off as we go to walk out we almost slip and fall due to the excessive grease and lack of cleanliness. Worth $100 bill ? I think not. Never going back.

The waiter messed up our order not once but twice and tried to tell us that the dish was correct when it clearly wasn't. In all the time we waited for someone to show up a manager never came to see if there was anything they could do to make it right.
I would rather just come here for dessert!!! I've had dinner a couple times here it's ok, better place for dessert

Went to the cheesecake factory on Friday for a date night with my husband.  It was packed as to be expected for a Friday night. They said the wait was 40minutes and our buzzer went off 40minutes later so they were pretty spot on.  I got a Malibu bay breeze which was made perfect. The bread was delicious.  We did not get any appetizers.  For our main course I got a Ceasars salad which was a very large so there was enough to bring home for lunch the next day.  My husband got a grilled chicken avocado club sandwich which he thought was delicious.  Of course we ordered dessert (who comes to the cheesecake factory and does not get cheesecake? ) I ordered a slice of their oreo cheesecake and my husband got their chocolate mousse cheesecake. The oreo was not my favorite, but still good. It had oreo in the center. The chocolate mousse cake was delicious.  Very rich and creamy. The big downfall was it took over 15minutes to get our cheesecake. Overall good experience and good food

Love this place, I will usually go in with some friends when going to the freehold mall, service good but something's might be salty at times, other than that great food, and cheese cakes not much more that $7-8 depending which you choose,
Over rated Loud factory is the correct word Been to the original in California -- mass production

I used to rave about the incredibly friendly service at this location, but they must have had a seriously off night tonight. My family (party of 6) arrived around 4:30 PM on a Tuesday afternoon. We walked up to the hostess stand, and the man behind it was on the phone. We weren't even acknowledged until finally, a waiter stopping by to drop off menus asked if we were being help. Of course, we had to wait for the man on the phone to finish before he could assign us a table. It was early in the evening on a Tuesday so the restaurant was near empty! At the table, it took a few minutes for our waiter to stop by, and we ordered drinks while looking at our menus. A while later, our orders were taken, and our waiter told us he'd be back with our drinks and some bread. It was at least 5 minutes and possibly nearing 10 until we receive our drinks and waters. It was another 15 minutes later before we received our entrees (we ordered 4 Bang Bang Chickens, 1 Spaghetti Carbonara without anything but pasta and broccoli, and 1 Veggie Burger - the only "first time trying" entree of the bunch). First came two of the four orders of Bang Bang Chickens. To be polite, we decided to wait to start eating since we figured the other chicken dishes wouldn't be too far behind. About 4 minutes later, another chicken dish and the pasta were delivered. Our waiter stopped by about 5 minutes later asking how we were enjoying dinner, and we told him that we were still missing another chicken and the burger. So 3 minutes later, the last chicken dish arrived. It wasn't until we asked again that we received the veggie burger 3 minutes later. So a total of 15 minutes between the first and last entrees were delivered!! If only the food was worth the wait. Unfortunately, the brown rice was near inedible. I understand it's challenging to cook brown rice, but the pieces on the plates were clearly scraped from the bottom of the pot. Not the delicious crispy bits, but the rock solid pieces that would break or stick to your teeth, if you dare try to bite it. About half the rice on each plate was spit out/pushed aside so we looked around, and our waiter was nowhere to be seen. When he finally came over, he listened to our concerns and said he'll send a manager over. The restaurant was still pretty much empty, but it took at least 5-7 minutes for the manager to arrive. In the end, one of the chicken dishes was remade and new side orders of rice were delivered for the others. The rice was still subpar, but at least it didn't feel as if it'd break your teeth. As for the other dishes, the spaghetti carbonara seemed much less flavorful than usual, and the veggie burger literally tasted like nothing. I was so disappointed about the burger because I strayed from my usual chicken chili to try something that I wouldn't normally make at home. I've had flavorful and tasty veggie burgers in the past but literally had to douse this one in hot sauce and ketchup in a failed attempt to impart some flavor into it. We paid the bill (nope, no reduced charges for the horrible, frustrating experience) and vowed to avoid this restaurant at all costs in the future. FOOD: 1/5 ENVIRONMENT: 3/5 SERVICE: 2/5 VALUE: 1/5 OVERALL: 1/5

The food is always phenomenal but the service is sometimes lacking. I come here sometimes when I visit the mall with my family. We usually start off with their ahi tuna tartar which is my personal favorite appetizer. We also get the nachos which is big enough to feed 8 people with one order!!! It is absolutely humongous. For the éntrees, the Miso salmon is unbelievable. It isn't dry at all and is flavorful. The Thai lettuce wraps are delicious with a nice crisp lettuce and juicy chicken. The lettuce wraps are also very big and colorful. The pastas are always a safe choice. Some of my recommendations are the Louisiana Chicken Pasta, the carbonara, and the Da Vinci are mouth watering. Lastly, you can't go wrong with their cheesecake. Their is a very big variety of cheesecakes and they are all sensational.  The only problem I have is the service. I would say that 3/5 times I come here, the service usually is pretty bad. If you are lucky, you might get a refill on your water. But I have had waiters and waitresses that have been very attentive.  I would recommend you to at least give this place a try and is definitely one of the better chain restaurants!

Not the first time I've been disappointed. Probably the worst service I've experienced at a restaurant. Maybe they aren't used to a party of 12.. But it took an hour to get our food, it all came out room temperature, the bread was stale (normally my favorite bread) we did get there at 11, so maybe it was yesterday's bread. Had to call our waiter over for more coffee, and ask that plates be cleared, so that we had room. The only thing that was good, was the taste of the food.. Would have been so much better if it was hot, though. Last chance I give Cheesecake.

The wait to be served was thirty minutes...my family and I pretty much enjoyed what we ordered, the plates are large. I had the sweet tamales on the appetizer menu...it was good however they could have been easy with the sour cream and all the sauce that came on top of them.  My husband had the ribeye considering they don't specialize in steaks it was soft and juicy, the only thing was that it was to to salt.    The girls had a burrito and really enjoyed it.  I would def. go back.
