Cheesecake Factory is always our go to place.. We love the food everything is always great. However we had a terrible experience tonight with our server Lou. I understand he was new, but we didn't get bread until after our appetizers .. My mother at another table got seated the same time and finished 30 minutes before me. I was on my second drink before actually getting my app. Lou was very nice, and handled all situations well, we saw he was busy.The chicken was chewy I took 3 bites and wrapped it , hopefully someone in my house will eat it. The food was not even hot, just warm. I hope the next time I come back I get better service & quality
Good food at the mall.  This is difficult to find but Cheesecake factory pulls it off!

Arrived at 6:35. Told we would have a 65-80 minute wait. At 7:50 we were told it would be any minute. I approached the counter a couple of minutes after 8:00 - my pager went off at that instant. I handed it to the hostess and several other guests handed theirs in AFTER me. We stood there for 5 more minutes while four parties, whose pagers where handed I after ours, were seated. After being ignored for another couple of minutes we walked out. Great customer service Cheesecake Factory and thanks for wasting more than an hour and a half of our time...
Food is as good as like heard. Can do a better job.  Love the cheese cakes though. I wouldn't suggest this place if you want you eat nice food.

Came here two weeks in a row. Both times I was very impressed with the polite greeting and an efficient seating process. Both times we received excellent service: prompt, attentive, polite. The food was great too! They have an impressive menu of light dishes and a full kids menu. There is something to satisfy any taste or dietary need. The decor and ambiance are equally pleasant. If I'm in the area again, I will definitely eat here again.

So we went to Cheeecake factory for the first time on a date night.  It was a little crowded but only 30 minute wait, on a Saturday night not bad.  We had a great time food was good my only complaint is the lighting, why is it so dark in there? It seems like a family place but is lit like a romantic place.  We had potstickers, tacos, a BBQ burger (awesome!) and lemon raspberry cheesecake and let me not forget a margarita :). Will definitely be back!

I've had mostly good experiences at the Cheesecake Factory. Last night was my first and last visit to their Freehold establishment. I sit at the bar and the person behind the bar hands me a menu. She then tells me it's happy hour and the draught beer is a special. Hearing this I order a beer. Before pouring my beer she turns and asks me if I'd like a 16 or 22 oz. I say, I'll take a 22 oz. When I ask to pay she charges me $9.50 for the beer. I'm in shock when I hear the price and ask her why she charged me so much. She tells me because the 22 oz. is not included in the happy hour pricing. So I end up paying an additional $5 for 6 ounces of beer.  She has to be the worst person behind the bar I've ever encountered. She made a few extra dollars for her employer at the cost of a customer and tip.

Great desserts of course but also so many great options of food.  If it wasn't a chain place  you would say the plethora of items in their menu is over kill but even then it's still a little much.  The appetizers are all amazing and the Mac and cheese balls are the best j have ever had. Same as any other Cheesecake Factory but just with great service!
Dishes are too salty and you can go to a diner for cheese cake on rt9 at manalapan  for half the price and twice the size and just or better in taste

I went with the Jambalaya over rice instead of pasta.  This was the bomb with a bit of heat, but not too much to scare away those look to avoid an inferno. The was chicken, shrimp and a bunch of veggies.  This is definitely a meal I would get on my next visit.

I would write a satirical piece on this establishment, but, that would be like trying to blow dry your hair in the rain. It's just not worth it. Worthless, in fact. This is the most mediocre place I have ever been. It reminds me of wearing black leggings and a t-shirt. I would definitely go back though.

If you are a vegetarian and there is meat in your salad BEWARE!  Don't bother sending it back, they will hide some type of gross meat in your food.  I don't know what that was and shocking neither did the waitress.  Shameful and gross.
No bad but lots of hype. I would stick with the apps and the drinks. Salads were wilted and over dressed. I love the brown bread so just choose dishes carefully or just drink! :)

Always love this franchise of restaurants. Anything you order here will not disappoint. I usually go for the same thing since I do not live close to a Cheesecake Factory location so it's rare that I eat here. The four cheese pasta is great and my usual order. This last time I tried the Cesar salad and I loved it. The only change I would make is dressing on the side. This location in particular is always great to eat at. The servers are friendly and there's never too long of a wait.

My wife and I stopped in at 11:25 on a Saturday morning and were asked to wait as other customers whom had also been asked to wait were sitting on the bench at the door. This surprised us as they had one section open and it was only 40% full. The vast majority of the tables were empty and we were asked to wait, no excuse for that. Then when we were seated,before the other party whom had arrived before us, we were seated at a table that had not been cleaned. We asked to seated at another table and our request was honored. Our waitress was very good, but the food was below average to downright poor quality. I had one piece of toast that had not been toasted and my wife's toast was toasted on one side. I saw a lot of plates that were not empty indicating it was not only our food that did not live up to TCF standards. The restaurant did not look ready to open and should not have been opened if not ready. There appeared to be enough staff, just a complete lack of direction. Avoid this place and     eat  elsewhere.

I love cheesecake.. The only downside is that on the weekends Friday and Saturday night the wait can be up to 3 hours! Its really nice when you can sit outside in the summertime .. Their chicken ceased salad is always my favorite...love love this place.. A little pricey but big portions so I think its worth it

I really enjoy coming to this mall and this restaurant. I love the variety on the menu. They are always busy and getting a table on weekend nights can be a lengthy wait time but I always think it's worth it. I've had super fast service and super slow service either way I enjoy munching on the bread basket and surveying the pretty atmosphere. There is allot of seating but can be really loud at peak eating hours. This may sound strange but I've have a few not so good cheesecake slices on more then one occasion, now I just don't order any cheesecake.

Idk what's worse, the fact that I waited on hold for 15 minutes to place a To Go order before hanging up or that I was stupid enough to go in and order in person and believe the "15 minute wait". So far we are on 25 minutes and nobody has spoken to me since they finally showed up to take my order.  I get it, you are busy but that's something that was expected. It's not like your staff was blindsided by a dinner time, Christmas shopping rush. NEVER AGAIN!

I have been goin to cheesecake factories for many years and the only reason I keep giving this location business is cuz it's in my hometown. The taste of the apps/entrees from this location to the others for some reason is night and day. Other than that, the cheesecakes and staff are amazing and that probably a part of the reason I keep going back.

Ate here for Father's Day with a few of my friends, I ordered a very simple dish, angle hair with marinara and small shrimps. The food took over 50 minuets to come out when ordered, and everyone's dish was right except for mine. They brought me a dish off the child's menu. Bow tie pasta with marinara sauce and jumbo grilled shrimp. So I politely told the waitress that this was not what I had ordered, and she took it back. Ten minuets later I received what looked from afar to be the correct dish, but when she set the plate down the noodles were regular Spaghetti noodles and the shrimp were way undercooked (which is hard to do since shrimp only takes about 30 seconds on each side!) So AGAIN I explained what was wrong and sent the food back. About 8 minuets later the correct dish FINALLY comes out. I take one bite and the noodles were still crunchy! So finally I was so frustrated and still starving that I said just take it away. I asked for the manager who came over and didn't even offer to comp my meal. I had to tell her I wouldn't be paying for that meal to get her to take it off the bill! This wasn't the first time I had issues at this Cheesecake Factory but I decided to give it another shot! Bad idea. NEVER EAT HERE. The managers are rude, they don't care about their customers and it's always ridiculously loud inside. Wish I could give it a -1 Star!

Very tasty burger, we both has the Smokehouse BBQ and the Mushroom Burger! One of the best I have had!! Service was friendly, seated on terrace a bit busy maybe why food delivery was just ever so long, but not terrible, will going back when in the area!!

So here's the new recipe for the cheesecake factory cheesecake are you ready because I'm going to give you the secret ingredients- First you start using fake ingredients instead of real ones-then you double the price, after that add a heaping portion of fake whipped cream, and top it off with cutting the portion size in half.  This is the sad reality of the cheesecake at the cheesecake factory in comparison to the cheesecake that I had there five years ago.  Shame shame shame in the height of strawberry season to use frozen syrupy strawberries too - insert heaping spoons of sadness here.  I'm sure they may be able to fool the average person, unless you're from Brooklyn and are a cheesecake connoisseur.  Then not so much.

I am currently here at Cheesecake Factory as of now I allowed myself to sit at the bar and there were maybe five other people at the bar. There are two people working the bar and I sat there for about five minutes before I got any kind of eye contact, I try to be reasonable because I get its a fast pace and busy business. There is a male and female working at the bar and she approached me and said "did he help you yet?" I replied "no". She apologized and took my order, took another ten minutes to get bread I ended up having to ask for it, then I proceed to ask for a glass of wine. She checked my ID and never ended up giving me the glass of wine I asked for. Every time I tried to get her attention it was a fail. When I received my meal (hibachi steak with mashed potatoes) my potatoes were still literally in whole chunks, I know they're "smashed potatoes" but I had literally had two quarters of a potato on my plate that I had to end up cutting up. Terrible service. Definitely will not be coming back.

I have been to several cheesecake factories, and this one unfortunately disappointed me.  I went here for lunch with my fiance, who has never been to a cheesecake factory before.  I puffed the lunch chicken Romano and he ordered the chicken tacos.   My meal was basically two small half sized chicken tenders and a pile of unflavored spaghetti that could feed a family of 4.  His"spicy" chicken tacos were bland with no sauce.  Very disappointing.   Okay, do you have top order cheesecake here, at least to go if there is no more room.  So we waited 10 minutes for the attention of our waiter, PETER.  then when we got his attention, we asked for the menu to look at desserts.  It took another 20 minutes to get the menu.  It took 10 minutes for PETER to take our to-go order.   Finally it took another 20 minutes to give us our doggy bags of cheesecake.   This was on a Friday afternoon.  We began our meal at 3:00, and finally left there at 5:30.  My legs were cramping and my butt fell asleep waiting so long.  So thank you PETER and cheesecake factory for this horrible experience, and so disappointed that this was my fiances first experience here

If i could give them zero i would of done that !!! We went there me , my husband and my daughter Sunday  around 4.30pm . I been in cheese cake factory's chain all over the country . This one are shocking . I ordered Mexican  salad and when they brought it i had one spoon and i got  this long hair !!!!!! Its gross !!!! I called one waitress and told her and she went and got a manager . The manager came and how worthless !! He said ( i went to the kitchen and made sure all staff have hair cover on !!!!  They need to be inspected by health department !!  He left and send another server to tell us the kitchen manager will re do the salad  himself !!!   Wooow , so only the kitchen manager can make something clean !!  I told him no thank you i want the check to leave . He said oh you didn't eat you font need to pay !!  Wooooow i left and went to PF change fir clean dinner .  I will call the health dept to report it .

Horrible on so many levels. I order ALOT of caterings I know every manger and edison and Lawrenceville. This place had an attitude since the moment I called this morning!! I called at 1130 for a small catering order for 4pm and they were we need 24 hour notice let me ask the chef. Mind you I've ordered caterings 100x from Cheesecake Factory and I call at 9am and pick up at 1130 all the time. I asked for paper plates and they refused till I insisted to just put 10 to go containers in my bag. When I got there even the lady in the to go area was so rude!!! I really don't understand what's wrong with this location but I see why it's a 3 star place. Should be 2 with all the attitudes. One lady behind me in line asked the person ringing her to help me with my bags that I shouldn't have to do it on my own. They have one guy working there who ended up helping me to my car who was nice. Honestly if your doing a catering Boston market people are soooo nice easy and convenient!! Also just look at my $17 chicken ceased salad honestly 4 little pieces of chicken won't cut it. ALSO I specifically said please make ONE tray veg out of the two chicken farfalle-- what do they hear??? No meat put it on the side. Negative.....Get your act together freehold get some new management and staff!! I have given the other cheesecakes over 20 grand in caterings and I hope I don't have to cater from you guys again :(

Although a crowd favorite at Freehold Raceway Mall, this Cheesecake Factory location disappoints on most levels.   First the good stuff, the exterior and interior decorations are really pleasant and attractive. The bar is really nice I have to admit. The atmosphere is terrific if you were shopping with friends and you want to eat, the menu is extensive, and when they deliver your food the portions are generous and the presentation is very good.  So you are expecting to have a really tasty, above average meal. Unfortunately when the food goes from your plate to your mouth, that's when you realize that the food quality is average.    Now that's not such a bad thing really, and would normally earn a solid three star rating. But the reason for the two stars, is simply the price, it's just too high for ordinary food. The price range for a typical meal is in the $15-$18 range. I believe it should be in the $10-$13 range. Because the food isn't priced to the quality, I'm forced to give a two star rating.   I ordered a shepherds pie which was ground beef and vegetables topped with mashed potatoes with a cheese crust. As exciting as it sounds it was just ordinary. My wife got a Mexican salad which again was presented in an exciting way, but the taste was just OK. Still it's a convenient stop if you were shopping at freehold Raceway Mall with friends and you're looking for a good environment with some good food. I just wish they would lower the price a little.

This is the first time I went to this Cheesecake Factory and it will be the last.   The whole lunch was a mess both in food and service, and I'm pretty easy going about restaurants.   To start, the server forgot to put my margarita in, so we actually received our food before my drink (it seemed to be pure sour mix, also).  My spouse ordered the apple cider and got regular apple juice.  The bread was so stale I couldn't even chew it. As for the food, my spouse is celiac and also has a black pepper allergy.  She ordered the coulotte steak.  It did appear to be gluten-free, since she's not sick, but she was worried because the server didn't seem to know how to handle the black pepper allergy.  The mashed potatoes were loaded with black pepper, which the server didn't state after being informed of the allergy.  The green beans also came with black pepper added on.  If she was informed of the black pepper on the sides, she would have ordered different sides.  The server did end up bringing brown rice as a side for her.  Screwing up allergies is dangerous and for that reason alone we'd be very hesitant to return, since no other area restaurants have had issues accommodating the black pepper allergy. I got the small plates of the fried veggies and one of the shrimp tempura.  The shrimp tempura smelled off and one bite proved the shrimp was off.  This was sent back.  Bad seafood can kill someone.  The fried veggies were good, but also impossible to screw up. Finally, my spouse asked for the mashed potatoes to be boxed up anyway for me.  Upon arriving home, I discovered that the server mixed the mashed potatoes up with the food she could eat.  Literally smashed and spread the mashed potatoes all over it.  This would have been gross, even if the server knew the mashed potatoes had to be separate due to allergies.  Also, I didn't get my dipping sauces included with my leftovers. We left a generous tip, because we always tip servers generously, but with the final straw of seemingly spitefully ruining leftovers with an allergen, we wish we just left 15%.  Honestly, the service deserved less.  We just never tip below that. Reading other reviews, we clearly aren't the only ones who had bad service there.  And to top it off, the place was almost entirely empty, which I thought was weird for a Cheesecake Factory but now I know why.

This honestly used to be my favorite place but from my last visit on Friday October 14, that will be my last. The only good part about it was that we were seated quickly and our server was very nice. But other than that the food was horrendous. I ordered chicken Marsala over some bow tie noodles and left there with a stomach bug. I was nauseous as ever and my stomach was killing me. I think we knew what happened next. With my left overs I offered to my friend that was with me. She felt fine after her meal. She got something different but her mom ate my left overs and she too produced a stomach bug!! I don't have a sensitive stomach and I'm not allergic to anything!! There is definitely funky going on with their food... and it's upsetting I couldn't enjoy it since it was an expensive meal! Wish this never happened bc this was one of my favorite places.

The food is great but sometimes just not worth the wait.  We pick up from here roughly 3 times a week, spend $60-100+ each time, and though you may not know me I probably know all the people at the pickup counter by face.  Some are great, get your food fast and check it but one is lazy beyond belief.  We ordered at 1:50 pm today, Monday, and were told the food would be ready in 25 min.  I came in at 2:20pm and defiantly beat any lunch crowd, it was fairly quiet.  The girl told me it was $80 and gave me the check to sign, I hate how Cheesecake makes you pay before you get your food because I can never figure out the tip (since you pay for the brief counter woman's service and doing so before gives no incentive to then give good customer service).  Either way I paid and was told the food wasn't ready and to just sit down and wait, mind you she never even checked my food order.  At 2:35, I got pissed off waiting for food that should have been ready when I came in and told the counter lady that.  She slowly finished the piece of cheesecake she was beautifying for someone and slowly walked off to get the food.  Surprise, it was ready and when she arrived back I asked to see the receipt I signed and left my tip on and turned it to $0.  JUST BECAUSE I ALREADY PAID YOU DOESN'T MEAN YOU HAVE A RIGHT TO TALK DOWN TO ME, TELL ME TO SIT AND WAIT, AND THEN IGNORE ME!
The bread was great. The spinach dip was good. Salad was not as good as it is hyped out to be. Cheeseburger was good but service was a little slow. Very nice bathrooms. Overall 3 stars.

One of our favorite places to go, whether it's lunch, dinner or Sunday brunch!  Although we wish there were more soup options, cheesecake is the best!  We have had excellent servers that we love getting over! Definitely recommend

Came here pretty recently and was pleased with the service. I attended happy hour and ordered a glass of wine and a cosmo. Cosmo was allitle sweet for my liking but it was good. The wine was fabulous. The nachos I ordered werent the best I ever had, but i was pleased with them.

Decent place to eat and you get decent portions as well as reasonable prices.... I usually do not eat out at National Franchises such as this establishment because I prefer to eat local and give my money to the local economy. But all in all decent place.

Well my daughter wanted cheesecake for her birthday so Red Velvet was great she said so mission accomplished. But always disappointed with weak $12+ Mojitos. Not worth it. Was going for the fish tacos which have been pretty good before but eggplant parm sounded so good. The eggplant pieces were either hard or rubbery. Also a slab of spaghetti stuck together and partially coated with pesto accompanied the bad eggplant. I mentioned the eggplant being undercooked to our server and he said that's the recipe and to ask to cook it longer next time. Service was good. Overall overpriced drinks and just adequate food - others had good steak tacos, good chicken marsala.

Love the very large selection of food, staff always seems to be very polite, happy and helpful. I would definitely recommend eating here if you are in the area an the cheesecake is to dye for lol ,...,..................................

Okay, we came here for desert. I got the Godiva cheesecake. It was very good. A great place to go to ruin your diet. Staff (this time) was very friendly. We sat down right away (which is a rarity in this place). My biggest complaint is that this place has a diner like menu. Typical 'jack of all trades, master of none' menu.  Truthfully - you can save some green and hit a local diner and get a comparable selection. This place is not cheap. But the cheesecake was good. Your green, your time at your own risk.

5 star service! 5 star food! Their bread is simply divine. Their tomato sauce is very chunky, I didn't like it because I only like sauce with a smooth consistency. Their penne is very flavorful. Their Parmesan is fresh as they grate it in front of you onto your plate. Their skinny menu is a great option as it has less calories with all the flavor!

Cheesecake factory is overrated they overcharge takes a while to get your food and hopefully bring the right items. There's a lot of other better restaurants in the area unless you like the cheesecake factory If you want to waste your money go for it. Best thing there is the CHEESECAKE

Like a 10 page menu and everything I've tried is good. I am a vegetarian I love their avocado stuffed hot eggrolls with dip,The stuff mushrooms, the portobello sandwich with sweet potato fries. My boyfriend had the chicken Marsala, he was very happy with it and it was a good size portion we had to take some home. The only disappointment I had was the chocolate layer cake everyone laughed at me and they were right I should've stuck to the amazing cheesecake selection my favorite is the turtle with Caramell and nuts.
Great service, great food. Didn't get an adult beverage at this location, but the soda was great! lol

What a large menu!  And really good portion sizes!   Great variety of salads and they will accommodate custom orders.  Recommend trying the vegetable French fries that included fried avocado, fresh portable mushrooms and zucchini! A real treat for the veggie lover and a nice change from regular fries.  What to watch out for: The facility can also be very cold, so bundle up!! We had light jackets on and we were still freezing. A negative here is the timing- reconsider if you are in a rush. our waiter disappeared near the end of our meals and took a very long time to bring the check to us.  Good think for our group is that we were not in a rush but it was strange that the waiter didn't come check on us for a 15 min period where everyone was done eating and the waiter seemed to have disappeared...

Very disappointed they should be ashamed to be open when they are out of half of the menu.  Manager offered nothing to reaolve an already unpleasant meal!!!  Will take alot to come back after this night.

Cheesequake Factory   5 star rating Cheesequake factory is amazing and delicious. Just how  good this place is is hard to put in words. I didn't like this place....I LOVED IT!! My daughter and husband went and came back to me with amazing feedback. They first got Buffalo wings, which they thought were O.K. Then, my daughter got the hibachi steak, which was the best part of the meal (to her). She thought it was AMAZING!!! The sauce that went with the steak was absolutely delicious! The steak also came with wasabi mashed potatoes , but she didn't want wasabi so she got regular mashed potatoes and they were also SOO delicious. The dish also came with vegetables such as mushrooms and chives/sprouts. My husband loves spicy foods, so he ordered the Southwest chicken sandwich, and he thought it was excellent!! Spicy food lovers, this sandwich is for you! The menu isn't just for steak and spicy food lovers. The menu has A LOT of choices to pick from. If you want salad, pizza, or anything, come to this place. Although my husband and daughter did not try the cheesecake this time, we have all tried it in the past, and it was very good. I definitely recommend this place, so please come here and I promise, this place will be sooo good!!!!!

We go here all the time because the food is great and the bartenders Patrick and Shelley are very friendly and professional. I usually get something from the skinny menu to keep the calories down so I can offset it with the cheesecake dessert.

Overpriced and service was terrible. We waited almost 20 mins for drinks after we were seated and then almost 40 minutes to have our order taken. The food was so so in fact I've been to many other places that could have given better portions and better food for way less .. vanilla bean cheesecake was ok kind of dry. Wouldn't be returning

What can I say but great food  the experience is always wonderful & the portions are always huge and the wait staff sometimes need an attitude change but other than that an over all experience is awesome we will definitely Keep going back

I've been here about 3-4 times and I can never say I genuinely enjoyed anything I have eaten. Overpriced, small portions and the food just isn't all that great. There is just far too many options on the menu for them to be consistent in each dish when cooking and I think that is the chains' downfall. Plus, the service is a little slow.  Only added an extra star because the cheesecake is always delicious.

Anyone that suffers from food allergies should stay away!!!!!!!!!Saturday evening I went there for dinner and ordered nachos for an app (told the server about my severe peanut allergy) then ordered my dinner which was pasta carbonara (spaghetti and bacon in a garlic cream sauce) once again told my server about my peanut allergy he let me know the kitchen was aware. So my pasta comes out and I had 2 bites of it and went to have my 3rd bite and saw what at first I thought was a big garlic clove.. I showed my boyfriend and he took it from me immediately and told me it was a big peanut. I was beyond shocked. I'm still shocked. Thankfully I didn't have a reaction. But my anxiety was so high that I thought I was.To me it was intentionally.. How does ONE FULL PEANUT end up in a pasta dish that doesn't even have peanuts in it in the first place. Also the fact that out of all items after alerting the server about my PEANUT ALLERGY TWICE theirs a PEANUT in the dish is way to ironic and suspicious. The manager didn't seem to be concerned or care just gave us his business card and said to call him later that night. Didn't even come outside to make sure I was ok or to say sorry while the EMS and POLICE came. Never in all the 26 years of suffering from this I NEVER had something like that happen. Please be careful going there to eat with allergies! My advice is to avoid completely. They clearly don't care about people's lives and think food allergies are a joke. I'm so sick to my stomach over this still. ZERO STARS!!!! So sickening....

The Cheesecake Factory is never my first choice, yet from time to time I find myself eating at one. During my two most recent visits, hunger and long wait times during peak brunch hours led me here. Apparently my fam and I weren't the only ones who wanted Sunday brunch at Turning Point... there was a 3 hour wait. In any case, the food here is just okay. Ambiance, complimentary pumpernickel bread and mojitos are more than okay, and I'm fine with that masking the lackluster food. Actually, some things on the menu are more than just okay as well. The avocado egg rolls have and always will be a winner. Next time, I'll need to remember to order these as my meal and not as shared app.  The reason I'm not in love with the food is because it's quantity over quality. Their menu is huge (literally, it's like a small novel). While it's great to have lots of options, they could stand to trim the fat a little, and focus on offering less dishes and preparing them really well. Besides menu selection, portion sizes are quantity over quality as well. I ordered a chicken salad sandwich and instead of serving me one delicious chicken salad sandwich, my plate was overflowing with four haphazardly assembled chicken salad sandwiches. Lunch here feels more like a cruise buffet. I'm just not that into it. I feel a little silly complaining... you sort of know what you are getting into when you visit a Cheesecake Factory. But, there are other chains that I like alot better and I think there are a few things that they could work on. Doesn't seem like their menu is changing anytime soon, so next time (because let's face it, there will be a next time) I'll have to be a little more careful about what I order.

The food is tasty, but they are shrinking their appetizer portions and charging the same. Just had dinner there and the apps were practically half the size...the same apps we get there at least a few times a month. They deny the change, but, since we've eaten there sometimes as often as twice a week in the past year, I know what amount I was served the last ten times I ordered the same dish.  Then there was a case of moldy bread that we were recently served (I have a severe mold allergy), which resulted in little in a way of apology from the manager.  Finally, the bottom of the bill includes pre-calculated tip amounts, which SHOULD be based in pre-tax bill, but in actuality are percentages of the total bill which includes tax. Now, I don't mind giving the waiter a little extra - we never tip below 20%, but I don't like to be misled like this. It should be my choice how much to give.  I'm a creature of habit, but I think it's time to find a new haunt.

Chicken samosas, spinach dip, artichoke - these are the tastiest appetizers that you can share with everyone getting some, nothing worse than they see 6 people at a table and they give you 3 appetizers to a plate so have to order more plates- I get why they do it. Miso salmon, chicken Madeira and chicken piccata- these are the 3 main entrées the family goes for, the servings are pretty big so at least half goes home. Sometimes if its just Mini-Me and I- we order a bunch of appetizers, split a salad and go right for the dessert... I make it a rule to hit The Cheesecake Factory and eat up- before we go buying any formal, semi formal, prom, wedding, bridesmaid dresses-- why you ask? well, won't you be eating where ever you are wearing the dress you decide to buy right? this just gives you a little breathing room. Frankly, whoever I have suggested this too has been, well surprised that I was right. I have not had to wait long to be seated, we tend to go a little bit earlier in the evening or at lunch - it can get pretty loud in there, especially when mommy groups insist on bringing their young children for lunch which is smack in the middle of nap time-so you are trying to eat with mini-meltdowns going off-- other than that-- service has always been attentive. We definitely eat at this CCF more than the one in Newport Beach CA, where we lived, but neither have the awesome view the one in Redondo Beach CA

Today, we dropped in for a late lunch.  We requested a booth , and waited extra time while they set it up.  When we sat down, two of the appetizer plates were dirty.  When the bus person passed, we asked for clean dishes which we got but  also abit of abrasive attitude.  Later, our meals came, one salad was tasty but the plate also dirty.  We sent it back and literally got a bowl of salad back.  All cheesecake factories are overpriced, high  calorie places.  This is poorly run as well.
The food is great. They're always accommodating to my food allergy. The wait is usually long so I love going around 4pm, or before lunch at 11am. The staff is always nice and knowledgeable.

My go to place for a great burger, salad, and other small plates when I'm in the area and want a clean predictable place. Clean is REALLY important to me. I prefer to sit in the bar area at a high-top, even when this place is packed, it's comfortable and service is predictable. Expensive and as a beer drinker I can vouch that on their best day, the draught selection is blah... Stella, Says Seasonal, Blue Moon.... Not bad beers, just boring.

Happy hour is great from 4-6 PM on Monday -Friday.  Drinks and apps reasonable.  However, beware of ordering a cocktail at any other time.  The price for a Cosmo was over-the-top at $13.99.  Also, they do not tell you what the price is until you get the bill.
I love Cheesecake Factory . The food is delicious and cake is always unbelievable!!! The service is always awesome !!

I love the idea of the Cheesecake Factory more than the actual experience. The food is very expensive, but the quality does not match the price.   The most recent time I was here I ordered Chicken Teriyaki. The chicken was poorly cooked and very tough. Moreover, the rice was unevenly cooked or "steamed," as I had hard grains mixed throughout. For the price, I expect that the food be excellent, but it is only average. The service also suffers; all servers seem miserable while working.

The Cheesecake Factory was delicious from past experiences but this time was a little different. When we were seated we found that the silverware was dirty, and we found that our Chicken Parm Pizza style came with extra plastic inside of it not to mention the pasta was cold as well. Besides those downfalls our dessert were terrific, and the Honey Truffled Chicken was cooked to perfection. Inattentive waiters long response times to our findings deserve two stars.

For big chain restaurant this gets 3.5 stars.  The best entree is their miso salmom but there are so many other very good options. If your looking for a quiet place this ain't it.  It's loud with lots of clingy clacking noise from silverware especially when sitting near the "Butler" areas.  However, with the right expectations this a very good family place with huge variety and overall solid and consistent tasting food.   The drinks are sweet and not worth the money but if you stick to the food your good to go.

Food was just ok... except for the chicken dumplings absolutely disgusting ... The biggest problem was the service my waitress  attitude (Jessica ) was so bothered to serve our food. Told her did not like an item and she rolled her eyes and took it away  never even asked to take it off the bill. Couldn't imagine if the place was busy how she must act .She will definitely keep us from going back !!!!

Let me first start by saying the host and hostess were very nice.  So not complaints there..And my waitress Erica .C. was ok/ attentive but The service was a lil TOO fast.. no time to digest your food for next course. With all that being said " The food was awful"! The sauces on the apps are bland....The fish and chips taste like nothing but grease. We asked for two Med well to Well burgers, they were raw!!  The pasta just tasted like oil. We told the waitress and she said she told a manager but he didn't come til I had to ask.  When he did, he told me to look for him next time I come. HUH?? Told him there would not be a next time. Oh! btw the waitress next asked us if we needed change so my parents just said forget it and let's go. They will chuck the extra $14.00..(We wanted to leave $25 but she got $39.) HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO ME!! Never again!! Keeping in mind I have celebrated my Birthday there for 6 years in a row when I lived in Atl..those dinners was not this experience.. at all!!

I've been here multiple times in that past and after a long 5 year hiatus,  twice in the span of two weeks.  Overall the food and service is not bad. Like many reviewers noted, the portions are humongous! After eating here, then eating at another restaurant, it makes you feel gypped and question the value of food at other places. There's good amount of food, but does it taste good? For the most part its hit or miss, with such a big menu, there has to be! After many visits here, these are the dishes my family would order:  avocado eggrolls, thai lettuce wraps, artichoke spinach dip, chicken madeira, masala chicken, shrimp with Angel hair pasta, factory chop salad, cobb salad, oreo cheesecake, white chocolate raspberry truffle cheesecake, chocolate tower truffle cake, & strawberry shortcake. This place is great for kids - only of you come early, which shouldn't be a problem since they usually eat early.  Otherwise, you'll have to endure a long wait. The food from the kids menu are just ok. They'll eat it, especially if they want dessert! It's loud, so if your kids are acting up, no one would really notice too much. There's also an area by the hostess to park your stroller! With the nice ambience, you don't feel like your roughing it by going to a Friday's or Ruby Tuesday's. I can see why many reviewers are disenfranchised by the wait time and occasional service issues. Those issues are minimal when you eat there early. There's a lot to like - the menu has a huge variety for the most pickiest eater, there's a good salad variety and some gluten free items, reduced calorie menu,  an outdoor patio, there's a bar, there's a nice selection of cakes, cheesecakes and some ice cream as well.  This will never be my first preference to dine in if given a choice, but it's not bad for large parties, drinks (no experience with this) , outdoor dining, for salad, the sweet tooth, and for families with young kids.

Long wait. Slow service! Mediocre food..just another chain. I prefer diner food. If you're looking for a good meal don't go here. Even outback is a better choice. Not worth your time or money. Please take my advice!!

You must try every single slice of cheesecake!  This place is amazing.  Take some home, freeze them, and try them directly out of the freezer....trust me!  It's almost as if creating a different type of dessert, but with all of the same, amazing flavours.  It's basically like a cheesecake ice cream cake  .        I haven't tried much of anything other than the dessert, but from what I remember it was good and it had an extensive menu selection which also included an alternative, healthier section.

location: Staten Island, Staten Island, United States
review: This was my first experience at the Cheesecake Factory and I can honestly say that it will be my last. This is also my first yelp review; today is a big day for me.  After constantly having to wait to get a table and for our waiter to acknowledge us and take our order we finally place our order and begin another long wait to get our food. After about 20 minutes are waiter tells is that we are just waiting for the salmon ordered by a member of my party, no big deal.  They finally bring out our food and the salmon was burnt and my meal is missing (I ordered chicken). After 5 minutes of trying to find our waiter he comes over and tells us that they gave my meal away to someone else and they are making another. After a thinly veiled apology he tells us the manager will come over and talk to us (he never did) and disappeared.  Overall a horrible experience all around and I will not return
Been here twice not only was the service beyond terrible both times, the second time I got food poisoning

The food, and especially the cheesecake, are absolutely delicious. I frequent here often. Wait times can be long, and wait staff can be slow during prime time, so try to go during off hours. There has yet to be a Cheese cake I haven't absolutely loved!

I should have read the reviews about this place before deciding to eat there. I picked up a few slices of cheesecake to go and it was horrible. I arrived home and after eating a quarter of the cheesecake found a hair hidden under a strawberry. The hair ruined the cheesecake and my appetite. I threw the rest away afraid to find something else and lost out on $23.  Safe to say ill never return.
The avocado egg roll is wonderful, it would be six star if they put them on salad bed than the white fried something. Another good news is they sell the brown bread, only 4 dollars, my favorite...
I found this dinner to be tasteless even with the watery salsa offered with the plate.  I thought it would have at least some cumin or chipotle seasoning on the chicken.

I decided to go to Cheesecake Factory because they make my favorite dish...Orange Chicken. I ordered it and it arrived. It was the lunch special so it was a smaller portion. The chunks of chicken appeared huge, about the size of golfballs. I cut open one chunk only to find a small piece of chicken engulfed in batter ! It was a golfball size piece of batter. They should have called it "orange flavored batter". What a disappointment. The orange glaze was delicious as usual but the chunks of chicken were so disappointing. The menu is very extensive but this was my favorite until now. I order the chicken pot stickers and the chicken inside vas very good but the sauce they used had a tart vinegar flavor. I guess I'll go there only for their cheesecake from now on.

Cute, hipster like atmosphere, with a large variety on the menu. Staff is friendly, and know how to serve customers. The reasoning behind this 4-star review rather than a 5-star is because of the large portion appetizers. Other than that, I enjoyed their chicken piccata entree, bedazzled with a creamy lemon sauce. The dessert is the best part of all- So many cheesecake flavors that it will take you a century to decide! :)

Got here before 5 and there is NO wait! Usually it's 45 minutes or longer. Haven't been here in a long time but have a gift card to use. Prices are not reasonable except in the small plates specials and the "Renee Special" which comes with turkey sandwich, salad and a bowl of soup! It's a great deal for $13.00! So much food!

First let me say the my family and I love the Cheesecake Factory. The variety, quality and overall experience at the CF. But the last trip went very very wrong.  Our waiter seemed "off" and we don't go to chain restaurants expecting someone to treat us like royalty or kiss our behinds we just want fooooood.  He wouldn't let us customize our order. Nothing too crazy but rather exchange side "x" for broccoli for example. He wouldn't do it! Dude it's just broccoli instead of "x".  Well I guess not today from the order patrol sheriff. It gets better they lost our ticket or something and we were there for an hour no apps no entries no refills for an hour. He didn't bother to check on us or our order we had to flag him down. Our orders finally come out and yea it's sup par even for a chain restaurant. I order pizza and it was raw on the bottom. Check my picture   The pizza always has a char on the bottom. We were frustrated and I guess the manager noticed and came over and spoke to us. That's the only reason I'm giving two stars and not one.

The food was just so-so. Cashew chicken fatty & dissaponting. Shrimp tacos kind of bland. Spaghetti & meatballs a 2 out of 10.  If you are just going for the cheesecake, then ok.  We were are party of 8, 6 of us got our food & 2 were left without entrees for 20 mins. Nice ambiance. I wouldn't go back.

This restaurant takes advantage of location. food is average. We just waited 40 minutes for 2 apps, 1 entree and two kids meals. One of which was a raw dish. Manager showed no remorse and couldn't care less. Waiter was great but he had a tough hull to climb. Hit brio  instead. Won't be back.

We've been wanting to go to Cheesecake Factory for months, but never got around to it. Now that we finally got the chance, I was surprised. The food was amazing, the appetizers or 'snacks' were the perfect portions, and the cheesecake was (obviously) delicious! Everything was beautiful, too, and our waitress was kind. My only complaint is the waiting time. We sat down at around 2:30pm, and left at 4pm. We all ate very quick, and were a party of 3. It was a pretty ridiculous wait, especially when they turned the outdoor heaters off and we were hungry.
Not that good. Had Sante fe chicken salad and nachos for app. Salad lacks flavor in chicken and dressing. Nachos had cheese wiz or something.. Not good.. Won't return for the price they charge

I want to hate this place because it's a chain restaurant but every time I go I'm always satisfied. The drinks are perfectly mixed with the amount of shakes. A martini received a certain amount of shakes that gives it that nice little ice 'Jimmi' topping. Excellent! Too many food options to choose from but everything has always been either very good or excellent. Needless to say their cheesecake is sinful! Again it's a chain restaurant I know, but if you're in the mall shop stop off, fuel up and then spend!! Oh yeah, stop off for a massage on the upper floor near Macy's!

This is one of the busiest restaurant with wait times to more than an hour at times. Service is sub par as they are so busy. Wait for table, wait for service if you need drink refill. Food is decent. It used to be good but now its just ok. Dessert is the best so if you are just craving for Cheesecake, just take out a slice and eat at home so you won't get frustrated with the dark busy noisy place. I bet they don't care about reviews to be honest as they are always busy anyway so they are making money.

If I could give zero stars I would. First it took 15 minutes before anyone came to the table to take our drink order. It took another 10 more minutes to get the drinks. Soda an water no bar drinks.  We had placed the entire order at the time of the drink order. The appetizer then arrived 15 minutes after the drinks when the waitress announced she would be leaving for the day and someone else would be taking over. 10 minutes more passed and we were asked if we would like drink refills to our empty glasses.  15 minutes more and the entrees finally arrived, ice cold tacos, cold stuck together rice and ice cold beans, gross and a cold undercooked pizza. Being a person who once worked in the restaurant industry I never complain but I could not let this go by. The waiter was nice and the manager came over and apologized and offered to have it remade and a complimentary piece of cheesecake.  Why would I want it remade to wait another 45 minutes and god knows what might be next.  By the time the ordeal was finally over it was 90 minutes of plain torture and $100. Disgusting and disappointing.  Never ever coming back.

Waiting a while for dinner here is honestly worth it. Their prices aren't super high and there is always something to please even the pickiest eater on the menu. The last time I went there was a special for a "pizza" of chicken parm with a large chicken cutlet and a pile of pasta on top. Very decadent and filling, but I love having the leftovers for lunch the next day! My boyfriend ordered the Hibachi style steak and it was also delicious.
one of my favs.  good service and good server.  bread was on point.  meal was good.  server went out of way to make my date happy.    a good time.

Dirty , Food Handling is disgusting, Kids running the show, Managers inexperienced . This place is an absolute disaster. Wednesday afternoon my family went to cheesecake factory they cook my sons cheeseburger way too well when they returned it came back with the piece that he had bitten out of it on the same burger when my wife asked the waitress to get the manager the managerThe manager said that he was sorry that he would give them a free milkshake why would they want a free milkshake when they brought back the same burger with the same piece eaten out of it with the cheese melted over . Absolutely a disgrace

Every time I give them another chance, I'm even more disappointed. This time I need to let them know.  I can't begin to explain how poor the service is at The Cheesecake Factory in Freehold. They just DO NOT CARE about their guests. At my most recent visit, after waiting for about 20 minutes to be sat (no biggie) we waited an additional 20 minutes before we were even acknowledged after being sat at our table. I had to actually get the waitresses attention and even then, no apology or explanation. She just did not care. The people that sat down after us, were waited on AND their food was brought out before we even had a chance to place an order. I was so aggravated, we got up and left. The people next to us were in shock as well. Such a huge disappointment! Was looking forward to a nice meal and instead we got treated like crap. They need a clean sweep of the people that work their. They really need to train their employees on customer service. And tell them to SMILE! That would help! Ugh! So annoyed!

I love their very diverse menu. The food is generally good but the service is sometimes off. Today we had to wait Five minutes for the host to figure out who was on duty. Once we were finally seated we had to wait even longer for a waitress to notice our existence. Not a pleasant experience. Will probably not come back.

I've been going to this cheesecake since 2010 and never really had any positive experiences that made me want to go back. I always get dragged here since its attached to the mall. Ive had waiters spill drinks on our table, be rude and ignore us, drop knives on me, and adding things to our bill that we didn't order over the years. So Ive always known what to expect But I was surprised when I came back here recently while the patio was open and was impressed by how friendly everyone I interacted with was. We came for a post shopping quick lunch and it was great. The food was good, the people were nice, no one spilled anything. This place has changed over the years for the better.

I usually love going to Cheesecake Factory but this experience was horrible.  Took 15 minutes to get our drinks.  We got 3 little butters with the 2 loaves of bread they gave us.  Took about 35 minutes to get our food after our appetizers.  My Parmesan herb crusted chicken was sitting in a puddle of oil in the plate along with the somehow soggy yet over cooked chicken.  Our shrimp was over cooked and rubbery and looked like slop on the plate with the garnish.  Really pissed off after paying over $100 for a meal I could eat half of.  Don't plan on going to this location again anytime soon

Everything was great. Food was excellent, drinks were perfect, the place is clean, etc. We came at an off time where it wasn't busy and choose to sit inside. I wasn't paying attention as I followed my bf and the hostess to the table. When I looked up, she had put down the menus next to or really on top of a table w a couple and their 1yr old! Ok, so by the time I looked up the hostess walked off and I felt so rude to ask for a different table, so I didn't. But seriously, u see two people come in with out kids it's the middle of the day, the place isn't packed was it really necessary to put us there??? I mean if they were on dessert then ok fine but they had just gotten their drinks. Annoying. Like have some common sense. Kale and Quinoa salad is my go to here. I love the lemon dressing it's perfect and the thin pieces of the lemon peel is so sweet and tender like the kale.  Avocado Eggrolls are always amazing. And the green sauce is so amazing!  Passion Fruit Mojito was also a win.   Other than the buz kill of a babbling one year old and all the commotion that goes the meal was great. The ambiance was just not right.

Good food good service. Menu is way too big but once you get through it the food is always decent. Consistent and you'll always know the quality you are getting. Fairly fast service so if you are in a rush and you don't have to wait for a table this is a good option. Its also convenient when when with several people because there is something for everyone. Sucks they only have breakfast on Sunday at a certain time but oh well.

This place is always a go. We love everything on the menu. Con: No ability to make reservations. They call you with the buzzer and then make you wait again in a separate line which never makes sense. Food is worth it just try to go for late lunch as its usually not too busy.

On the positive side the tie ra appetizer and mushroom soup are fantastic. We got the fish tacos and I told them I can not have anything spicy so they agreed not to put anything hot in there. It arrived with chipotle sauce so I returned it. It came back without chipotle sauce but was full of jalapenos which I bit into thinking it was safe.the last time I did that I was sick for a year because I cannot have hot peppers. By that time we had to leave.

A tradition with my kids, the NYE dinner at Cheesecake Factory.  Everyone tried a new dish and each of them were good. The Pasta Carbonara was the table favorite but the Calamari disappeared almost immediately :).   All the Cheesecake deserts didn't disappoint either.  Always a good meal and you definitely leave feeling full, even with 3 teenagers!!!
Went to cheesecake for the first time. And was beyond impressed with the food and more importantly the service provided. The staff was friendly and very accommodating

I haven't been here in years and now I know why. We went on a Sunday afternoon, got here at 1:35 pm and was told there was no wait for 2 people... 10 minutes later we were sat. There was a brunch menu available until 2 pm. We knew what was wanted prior to sitting down. Our waitress came over 10 minutes after we sat and said she was busy and would be right back. She came back at 2:04 pm and took our order and then said we could no longer order from the brunch menu. After stating that we had been sitting for over 20 minutes, she spoke to her manager and they allowed us to order brunch. Our food arrived burnt, cold and thrown together on a plate. The fried chicken was soggy and wet. The waffles couldn't even be considered waffles. It looked like they scraped off what was left on the waffle maker and threw it on a plate. To top it off, the dish costs over $16!!! I will never be going back here again.
